title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 2 (9-inch) unbaked pie crusts and bake at 350° until done.

title: zucchini bread or muffins
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together until lemon color.
Gradually add the rest of ingredients and beat well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan or muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: deer jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients; make orange size balls.
Place one ball between 2 sheets of waxed paper and roll out to desired thickness. Refrigerate 5 hours or overnight.
Peel off wax paper and place in food dehydrator or oven at 200°.
Baste with 1/4 cup water, 1/4 cup liquid smoke and squirt of maple syrup.
Turn every hour and baste for 4 to 5 hours or until crisp.
Cut into strips while still hard.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Add seasoning and mix. Add pecans and toss until all nuts are coated. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, turning once.

title: apple walnut raisin pie
directions: Combine
apples,
spices,
sugar,
walnuts and raisins. Line pie
pan
with
pastry,
place apple mixture in pan.
Dot with butter; place top crust on and seal edges.
Cut slits for escape of steam.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: brown sugar chews
directions: Beat eggs. Add butter and brown sugar.
Stir. Add flour to mixture and stir thoroughly.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Pour mixture into pan and spread evenly.
Mixture will be slightly stiff.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes. Cool and cut into squares. Do not overbake.

title: fiesta crepes en casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery in frying pan. Drain. Stir in corn. Combine tomato sauce and taco mix in separate bowl, stirring to blend. Add 1 1/3 cups of tomato sauce mixture to meat and corn, mixing well. Spoon 2 tablespoons meat mixture onto each cornmeal crepe and roll to enclose filling. Spread remaining meat mixture in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place crepes, seam side down, on top of
meat mixture. Spoon remaining tomato sauce mixture over crepes.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes. Serves 10.

title: pimiento-onion relish
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir until sugar is dissolved. Add pimientos and onion.
Marinate overnight.
Drain and serve with meat.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop stems to make 1/4 cup.
Cook mushroom caps in margarine for five minutes.

title: hershey cocoa fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt and milk in large saucepan on medium heat.
Cook mixture for 26 minutes.
Test by dropping small ball into glass of water.
It is done when a soft ball forms in the water.
Then add remaining ingredients. Stir until thickens.
Then pour into greased pan.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat egg until light and beat into mixture until creamy.
Mix in the chopped apples and nuts.

title: homestyle dressing mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl and blend well.
Put mixture in a foil packet or a 1-pint glass jar and label as Homestyle Dressing Mix.
Store in a cool, dry place and use within 6 months.
Makes enough mix for 2 cups Homestyle Dressing (2 tablespoons).

title: strawberry get-up and go
directions: In blender, combine berries, milk, yogurt and orange juice. Blend smooth and pour into a tall glass.
Slip whole berry on the tip of the glass and you have a pretty, as well as a nutritious drink.

title: chocolate oatmeal chippers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Gradually add combined flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes or until set.
Cool 2 minutes on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Store tightly covered.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: arthur treacher's fish
directions: To remove fishy taste, slice lemon and place over fish.
Add just enough buttermilk to cover.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Heat oil in heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan.
Drain off milk. Cut fillets in half and dredge in flour.
In another bowl combine pancake mix and club soda until consistency of buttermilk.
Dip floured fillets into batter and let excess drip off into bowl. Deep-fry 4 minutes each side.
Warm in 250° oven until all are fried.

title: salmon-macaroni pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir together beaten eggs, macaroni in cheese sauce, salmon chunks, soft bread crumbs, shredded American cheese and salt.

Turn mixture into a greased 10-inch oven-going skillet or a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° until set in center, 40 to 45 minutes. Cut in wedges or squares. Garnish each serving with a parsley sprig.

title: scallops thermidor
directions: Cut large scallops in half.
Fry mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk gradually and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add scallops and parsley. Place in a prebaked pie shell (8-inch deep dish works best). Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake in a hot oven at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese browns.
Serves 6.

title: tropical drink
directions: Combine fresh ginger, water, sugar and cloves; bring to a boil, then simmer for 5 minutes.
Cool and allow mixture to steep for 6 to 8 hours.

Combine ginger mixture with orange and apple juices that have been diluted according to package directions and lemon juice. Strain mixture to remove ginger and fruit pulp. Makes 25 (6-ounce) servings.

title: eastern shore crab cakes
directions: Combine
crab
meat,
salt, pepper, eggs, butter, lemon juice and
Worcestershire
sauce	in a medium mixing bowl; mix well. Combine crab cake mixture with just enough bread crumbs to shape mixture into small cakes.

title: bake-off twenty-nine zucchini crescent pie
directions: In 10-inch skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In a large bowl, blend eggs and cheese.
Stir in vegetable mixture. Separate crescent roll dough into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 11-inch quiche pan, 10-inch pie pan or 12 x 8-inch baking dish; press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture evenly into crust.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes, or until knife, inserted near center comes out clean.
If crust becomes too brown, cover with foil during last 10 minutes of baking.

title: oklahoma chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients at one time.
Pour into a cast-iron skillet.
Bake only 15 minutes.
When cools, you'll have cake around the edges and pudding in the middle.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Beat on stove in double boiler for seven minutes.
Great to use with coconut.

title: old-fashioned corn bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let stand 1 hour. Add next 5 ingredients. Stir well. Bake at 400° until done.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt.
Set aside.
Bring to boil the butter, water, shortening and cocoa.
Pour liquid mixture over dry ingredients and beat.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Heat the first 4 ingredients and beat well.
Let this cool while you whip a large can of Milnot.
Now blend the strawberry mixture and cream cheese.
Pour whipped Milnot in also.
Mix together well and pour into crusts made from graham cracker crumbs.
Chill overnight.
Makes 2 pies.

title: zucchini and eggplant
directions: Saute garlic in oil.
Add vegetables in layers as order given, sprinkling each layer with 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Drizzle 1/2 tablespoon oil on top.
Cover.
Cook over low heat and stir occasionally.
Cook 35 to 45 minutes.

title: smokie link daffle
directions: In medium saucepan, combine gravy mix and water; blend thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and heat, stirring frequently, until sauce thickens and links are heated through. Can be kept warm by placing in a fondue pot or in a crock-pot on low setting.

title: greek salad("roselawn")
directions: Toss with crisp salad and fixins right before serving (tomatoes, cucumbers, carrots, radishes, broccoli, cauliflower, mandarin oranges, almond slivers, etc.).

title: dump salad
directions: Mix well and cover; store in refrigerator.
Ready to use now or will keep up to a week.
Ummmmmmmm good salad.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt butter into a 13 x 9 1/4 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Add the sugar
and crumbs.	Mix together and press into the bottom of the dish.
Add	the
remaining	ingredients
in
the order listed. Pour
the
condensed
milk over the ingredients last. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: poppers
directions: Wash peppers and slice in half lengthwise removing all seeds, being careful not to rub your eyes and wash your hands thoroughly when done.
Stuff each pepper half thoroughly with cream cheese. In med saucepan heat oil on med-high heat until oil is hot.
In a med size bowl mix all of flour with enough water to make batter consistency thick enough to cling to peppers.
Place poppers 6 at a time in hot oil.
Let cook until crisp turning over to cook both sides.
(New oil will not allow batter to brown as well.)
Remove cooked peppers from oil and drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups hot water; add berries and pineapple. Refrigerate until firm.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on top of pizza dough. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese.
Top with 1/4 pound grated Mozzarella cheese.

title: pork chop dinner in foil
directions: For each pork chop, put on 12-inch foil. Spread soup over surface. Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Arrange potato and carrot on top of meat.
Seal tightly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Can also be done on barbecue grill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: special k loaf(non-dairy)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a very large bowl, adding cereal last, and spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan lightly sprayed with Pam.
Mixture will be quite thick.
Bake at 350° for at least one hour.
May freeze before baking for later use. Serves 12 to 15.

title: english toffee cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolk.
Add flour and vanilla. Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Wet fingers and spread mixture over entire surface.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. While hot, sprinkle chocolate chips over and spread when melted. Top with nuts.
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook low to medium for 4 to 5 hours.

title: jelly roll cake
directions: In small bowl of electric
mixer, let eggs warm to room temperature, about 1 hour.

title: oatmeal crunch
directions: Cream butter with brown sugar, vanilla and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients, blending in nuts and chocolate chips last. Press into bottom of ungreased, 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: german slaw
directions: Layer cabbage, pepper and onion.
Cover with sugar and celery seed.
Heat vinegar, salt and mustard to a boil.
Take off stove and then add oil, then heat again to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Toss.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drain before serving. Makes a large dish for a family reunion, or will keep well in refrigerator for several days.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: First Layer:
Crush Oreo cookies in blender.
Save 1/2 cup for topping.
Melt oleo.
Combine cookies and oleo.
Put in 13 x 9-inch dish; let chill.

title: 6 single pie crusts
directions: Soften cream cheese and margarine at room temperature.
Add flour and mix with potato masher, then with hands.
Bake pie shell at 475° for 8 to 10 minutes, pecan pies at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or fruit pies at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: swiss 'n chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with walnuts, if desired.
Bake for 40 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Place in baking dish. Add both cans of soup, cheese, salt and milk.
Stir until mixed. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top and drizzle butter over this.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pineapple - ritz casserole
directions: Mix together pineapple and cheese.
Mix together in another bowl, sugar, flour and pineapple juice.
Add this to the cheese mixture.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Pour mixture in.
Melt the margarine and add to Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle over cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 25 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake frosting
directions: Cook until thick, then add 3/4 cup coconut, 1/4 cup nuts and vanilla.

title: *marinade for barbecued chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Wash and dry chicken pieces on a paper towel.
Place in a bowl.
Pour over the marinade.
Marinate at least 2 hours (overnight is even better). Baste and turn pieces occasionally.

title: lemon coconut bars
directions: Mix shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Stir in flour.
Press and flatten mixture with hand to cover bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch oblong pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: turtle noodle soup
directions: Boil turtle in water until meat falls off the bone.
Cut in bite size pieces and discard liquid.
In 6-quart pot, combine all of the ingredients.
Cook until vegetables and noodles are done.

title: cream pie filling
directions: In saucepan mix sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually add milk and egg.
Cook until thick over low heat, stirring constantly. Add vanilla and bananas or coconut.
Pour into baked pie crust or graham cracker crust and top with whipped topping when cool or meringue.

title: fruit cream cheese cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with melted margarine.
Press evenly in bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Let cool.

title: king cake(a mardi gras tradition)
directions: Put milk in small bowl and add the flavoring. Dissolve the yeast in the milk and set aside for a few minutes until foamy.

title: hawaiian beans
directions: Combine beans, ham and pineapple chunks.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with pineapple slices and sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: fried squash or zucchini
directions: Combine all ingredients, except squash or zucchini.
Dip squash or zucchini in batter and deep fry until golden brown. Drain on paper towel.

title: honey dog biscuits
directions: Optional:
You will also need bone-shaped cookie cutters.

title: sourdough bread
directions: In large bowl make stiff dough of sugar, corn oil, salt, starter, warm water and flour.
In larger greased bowl, put dough mixture and brush top with oil.
Let rise overnight (8 hours or more), covered lightly.
Divide dough into 2 parts and knead each piece on a floured board a few times.
Make into loaves and put in loaf pans with brush with oil to rise.
Let rise 6 to 8 hours, covered lightly.
Bake in bottom rack of oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: killer chocolate cake
directions: Combine cocoa and boiling water, whisking until smooth.
Cool completely.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and baking powder.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish, in oven.
Add ingredients and slice onions round on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients to first mixture and add zucchini.
Put in loaf pan and bake at 359 degrees for 55 - 60 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients
except
ginger ale.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: chocolate cream drops
directions: Thoroughly cream together butter, shortening, cream cheese and sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Stir in cooled chocolate. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to batter.
Blend well.
Stir in nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 bread pan.
Combine first 5 ingredients; use pastry blender to cut in shortening.
Stir in juice, peel and egg until moistened.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, Jell-O, cornstarch and water together until thick. Cool.
Cut up strawberries into baked pie shell.
Pour mixture over strawberries and let it set up.
Top with whipped cream, Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: sauteed cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 10-inch skillet.
Cook over medium low heat.
Stir until well mixed.
Cook for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: linda padula's pecan pie squares
directions: Set oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press firmly in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, beat Eagle Brand, milk, egg and vanilla.
Stir in chips and pecans.
Spread evenly over crust and bake for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into bars.
Store, covered in container.
Yields 36 bars.

title: peanut butter and potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add peanut butter.
Add flour, soda and vanilla (dough will be stiff).
Blend in chips and nuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.
My grandchildren love them.

title: butter barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter in a pan; add onion and cook until clear.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over brisket as in recipe to follow.

title: lemon pie
directions: Heat lemon juice in microwave and dissolve lemon jello. Prepare pudding with skim milk.
Pour cooled jello into pudding. Pour into pie crust.

title: taco sauce
directions: Mix ingredients.
Heat to desired thickness and can at 10 pounds pressure for 5 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: In a large bowl, mix all cheeses and sour cream thoroughly, with hands.
Add garlic
powder, seasoned salt, onion, and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix again.
Spread walnut pieces on cookie sheet or tupperware lid, sprinkle parsley flakes over walnuts. Shape cheese into desired ball and roll in walnut mixture until completely covered.
Add more nuts and flakes as desired.

title: pauline's peanut butter pie
directions: Brown pie crust.
Let it cool.
Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar until they are fine crumbs.
Put about 2/3 of crumb mixture in pie crust; set aside remainder of crumbs.
Next, combine cornstarch, 3 egg yolks, sugar and milk.
Blend well, then cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
As it thickens, add butter and vanilla.
Pour custard in pie crust and let cool.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over custard.
Let cool.

title: matt's salad
directions: Mix together pineapple with juice and dry Jell-O. Add cottage cheese. Mix well. Then fold in whipped topping. Chill.

title: ma's sausage pie
directions: Make sure there are no holes in crust.
Line a 9-inch deep glass pie plate.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix pork and beans, vinegar, brown sugar and ketchup. Separately mix beef and onion, then mix all ingredients together. Place in a 2-quart covered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil together cocoa, sugar, milk and margarine for 2 minutes. Add peanut butter, vanilla flavoring and oatmeal.
Drop by spoon on large sheet of aluminum foil.
Cool and serve.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients together.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to creamed ingredients.
Mix until well blended (2 to 3 minutes) and fold in walnuts.
Bake in angel food pan at 350° for 1 hour.
You can make this ahead of time because the more moist it becomes, the better it tastes!
Slice and serve with whipped cream!

title: fresh canned green beans
directions: Drain water from beans.

Rinse beans in can 4 times with water. Add enough water to fill can 2/3 full. Fry bacon until soft in small heavy skillet. Remove bacon from skillet and set aside. Add can of beans with water to hot grease. Add minced garlic, sugar, salt and pepper to beans.
Mix, then lay bacon across beans. Wash cabbage leaves and lay across to completely cover the beans. Cover with lid and cook on low for about 1 hour.
Remove cabbage and serve.
Makes canned green beans taste like fresh green beans.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk which has soda stirred into it. Lastly, add mashed bananas and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in 9 x 13 pan or 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 cookie sheet.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients with your hands.
Shape into small balls and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 100 balls.

title: magic crunch bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
Coarsely crush 3 cups cereal.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven. Sprinkle crushed cereal over margarine.
Top evenly with chips, coconut, Eagle Brand, nuts and 2 cups uncrushed cereal.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: apple muffins
directions: Mix all
ingredients together.
Batter will be thick.
Bake in small muffin pans 18 to 20 minutes at
350°; in large muffin pans for 20 -25 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Add peanut butter and beat well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in crust.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: special cookie cake (or dump cake)
directions: Mix all ingredients until batter forms. Place 3/4 of batter in an ungreased 13 x 9 pan, glass or metal. Distribute any flavor of fruit pie filling on top of batter, then dollop drops of remaining batter over the pie filling. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon-garlic chicken(low calorie)
directions: In a nonstick skillet, saute first 2 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, for 25 minutes or until done (cooking time is 25 or 30 minutes).
Serves one.
(I use green peas.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Divide ingredients in half.
Using a 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish, layer each ingredient starting with squash ending with soup. Then repeat layering process.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Slice the unpeeled orange into eight parts.
Remove the seeds. Place half the cranberries and half the orange slices in a food processor.
Process until the mixture is evenly chopped.
Transfer to a bowl.
Repeat with the remaining cranberries and orange slices.
Stir in the sugar.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: bread or rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and half of flour; beat 2 minutes.
Add egg and shortening.
Beat in remaining flour gradually.
Mix with hands until smooth.
Place in greased bowl.
Keep covered until double in size.
Punch down and shape into loaves or rolls.
Let rise and bake at 350° to 375° until brown.

title: linen whitener
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Soak table linens, pillow cases or clothing in this mixture for 30 minutes, then wash as usual.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter.
Rinse shrimp well.
Mix together all ingredients and form into a ball.
Cover with cocktail sauce and serve with crackers.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put cranberries in boiling water and boil for 20 minutes.
Put through a sieve and cook for 3 minutes.
Add sugar and cook for 2 more minutes.
Place in a bowl and add raisins.
Cool.
Add the nuts and just before it sets, add celery.

title: apricot glazed chicken
directions: Mix soup, preserves, dressing, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken parts in a flat pan.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 3/4 hours; uncover for another 1/2 hour.
Serve with rice, noodles and a salad.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix and spread in greased 8 x 8 square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tangy cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans; mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Shape into a ball and roll in pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken with rice
directions: In 9 x 12-inch ungreased roasting pan, mix and stir first 4 ingredients.
Put chicken on top of rice mixture and push chicken down well.
Cover dish with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry pretzel jello salad
directions: First layer:
Mix pretzels, margarine and 1/2 c. sugar together well and bake in a 9x13 inch pan at 350° for 10 minutes; cool completely.

title: cheesy beef pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and green pepper; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, mushrooms and seasonings.
Separate crescent rolls and press the triangles into a 9-inch pie plate to form a crust.

title: sweet and sour pork(total cooking time:  19 minutes)
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
Set aside. Place carrots and oil in 3-quart microproof casserole.
Stir. Cook covered on High (Maximum power) 4 minutes.
Add onion, green peppers and pork; stir.
Cook, covered, on High (Maximum power) 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a bowl, mix reserved pineapple syrup and cornstarch.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Add to pork, along with pineapple chunks.
Stir.
Cook, covered, on High (Maximum power) 10 minutes or until sauce has thickened and pork is done. Serve with rice or chow mein noodles.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cherry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten eggs.
Add milk in which soda has been dissolved.
Add flour, spices and salt mixture.
Add nuts and cherries; pour into a Bundt pan or 2 layers that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350°.
Ice as desired.

title: banana pop freeze
directions: Peel bananas; cut in half crosswise.
Insert wooden or plastic sticks.
Brush with juice.
Place on wax paper or cookie sheet and freeze until firm.
Melt chocolate in pan on low heat or microwave.
Cool slightly.
Spoon chocolate over bananas.
Roll at once in nuts.
Eat at once or freeze.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburg and onion in a large pot.
Drain grease.
Add sugar and chili powder.
Stir for a minute.
Add tomatoes, beans and vinegar.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Stir well.
Cook 10 minutes, tasting occasionally.
Add more vinegar, sugar or chili powder to taste.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Can be served with corn muffins.

title: greenbrier salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and marshmallows in boiling water. Let cool. Mash cottage cheese fine. Combine all ingredients. Place in a salad bowl and chill overnight.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Saute onion, shrimp and scallops until scallops are done. Drain and set aside.
Mix soup, mustard, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Heat on medium-low until hot, stirring often so it doesn't stick.
After thoroughly heated, add cheese, stirring until melted. Fold seafood into soup mixture.
Serve over rice.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Combine vanilla wafers, eggs and milk.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add pecans and coconut.
Combine with vanilla wafer mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° in oven in flat pan for 45 minutes.

title: fantastic frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy, add sugar, beating until smooth. Add peanut butter, mixing well. Stir in milk and vanilla. Fold whipped topping into creamed mixture. Pour into cooled crust. Sprinkle with nuts if desired. Freeze at least four hours.

title: guaranteed blue ribbon cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and set aside 20 minutes.
In another bowl mix the brown sugar, 1 cup white sugar, flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add the eggs and oatmeal mixture.
Bake approximately 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix and serve chilled.

title: peanut butter cookies(diabetic)
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into 1 inch balls, using about 1 teaspoon of dough for each.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork. Bake at 375 degrees for 12-15 minutes or light brown.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes almost 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and cream cheese.
Gradually add Cool Whip and sugar. Add vanilla.
Pour into one deep baked pie shell.

title: microwave bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High 7 to 8 minutes, stirring twice, until cucumber is crisp-tender and onion translucent.
Ladle into a glass jar. Cover, cool slightly and refrigerate.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Melt margarine, mix with crumbs and walnuts; pat into a 9 x 13 -inch pan.
Mix Cool Whip, frozen lemonade and milk.
Pour over crust, top with 2/3 cup of crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: jeanette carter's mother's egg custard pie
directions: Combine egg, sugar and salt.
Add milk, vanilla and nutmeg. Pour into pie shell.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes. Then bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted in middle of pie.

title: candy cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Mix in given order.
Drop and flatten.
Cool on pan for a few minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: jello and buttermilk salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water.
Cool.
Add buttermilk, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix well and let congeal.

title: no bake pumpkin pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine gelatine, spices and salt.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk and eggs, mixing well.
Let stand 1 minute. Cook and stir constantly over low heat until gelatine dissolves and mixture thickens slightly, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in pumpkin until well mixed.

Pour into crust. Chill until set, about 3 hours. Garnish with whipped cream or topping. Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg or as desired. Substitute 1 1/2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice for cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.

title: tropical punch
directions: Place ice cream in a large mixing bowl.
At low speed, gradually add fruit juices, then milk and mix until blended.
Pour into chilled thermos containers.
Shake or stir before serving. Yield: about 3 quarts.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: Pour oil in 7 1/2 x 12 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Place in oven to heat at 400°.
Cut steak into serving size.
Pound 2 tablespoons flour into each side.
Place in a heated dish with oil and turn to coat both sides.
Sprinkle on soup mix.
Pour tomato soup, mixed with water, over all.
Cover tight.
Reduce temperature to 325°. Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours until fork-tender.
Skim excess fat from gravy.

title: zucchini rice casserole
directions: Combine zucchini and yellow squash in bowl.
Place half of squash mixture in bottom of a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Add half the onion.
Sprinkle garlic salt and pepper over squash. Cover with half of the tomato bits.
Add all of rice.
Add 1/2 of cheeses and dot with 3 tablespoons margarine.
Repeat this layer, but no more rice.
Cover and cook for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cover with topping last 10 minutes of cooking.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Put onions, tomatoes and hot peppers in a large pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and then pour over tomatoes.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and immediately put in sterile jars and seal.

title: bean and beef enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray a large skillet with nonstick coating.
Add onion and ground meat.
Cook until done.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with nonstick coating.
Add 1/4 teaspoon garlic to each can of enchilada sauce.
Pour 1/2 can of enchilada sauce in the bottom of pan.
Follow one of these methods: Roll or layer.

title: triple cheese spread
directions: Place first four ingredients in a blender or beat in a deep bowl with an electric hand beater.
Season with Worcestershire sauce, garlic and pepper.
Beat until all is very smooth.
Remove to a plastic container with lid for storage.
This may be used as a spread on French bread, sourdough bread or rolls.
It's especially good on hot baked potatoes.
Serve cold with relishes and/or crackers.

title: apricot divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water and corn syrup in a 3-quart saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves. Cook over high heat without stirring until mixture reaches hard ball stage.

title: mimi's jello in a can
directions: Prepare lime Jell-O as directed.
Open pineapple, drain and pat dry.
Put pineapple back in cans.
Pour in lime Jell-O until full. Place in refrigerator until chilled.
Open bottom of can and push Jell-O out with lid.
Slice between pineapple.
Put small amount of Cool Whip on center of slice.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook cubed potatoes.
Set aside 1 cup potato water after draining.
Fry sausage with onion.
Do not drain.
Add flour, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Stir in 3 cups milk and the 1 cup potato water.
Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened. Add corn and cooked potatoes.
Cook until hot.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pizza pit salad dressing
directions: Blend onion, sugar and vinegar well.
Add paprika, celery salt and salt and blend well.
Add oil.
Blend well until well mixed. Makes 1 pint.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Saute butter, onions, bell pepper, garlic and celery.
Add 1 pound crawfish tails and tomatoes.
Simmer 5 minutes and stir. Add mushroom soup and water.
Cook five minutes.
Stir.
Add 3 cups of cooked rice.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Yum!
Yum!

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Turn off stove, cover and let sit for 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup cheese. Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese evenly over mixture.
Place in warm oven to melt cheese.

title: baked beans
directions: Cover and soak beans in cold water overnight.
Drain.
Add fresh water and steam for 20 to 30 minutes or cook on stove until done.
Drain and measure liquid to use in baking.
Add seasonings with liquid.
Pour over beans in roaster.
Cut bacon in pieces; brown in oven.
Pour into beans.
Bake at 350°, covered, until nearing done, then uncover for the last hour of cooking.

title: tuna cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 3/4 crumbs.
Form 6 patties, coating with 3/4 crumbs.
Spray Pam on cookie sheet and place patties on sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, or heat 2 tablespoons oil and fry in pan.
Flip and add another 1 tablespoon oil.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain and rinse kraut in cold water.
Mix with other ingredients.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Mix all ingredients well but don't overbeat.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 loaf pan and bake 45 minutes.

title: fern's dumplins
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Roll to desired thickness and drop into boiling broth.
If chicken wasn't very fat, add margarine to broth.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in loaf pan 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry ambrosia salad
directions: Mix all together in a bowl.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popped corn in large buttered roaster.
Boil margarine, sugar and syrup for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add soda, salt and vanilla.
It will foam.
Pour over corn.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring it every 15 minutes.

title: wedding cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix margarine, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and vanilla in 3-quart bowl.
Stir in flour, nuts and salt.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until set, but not brown, 8 to 9 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm. Cool; roll in powdered sugar again.

title: garlic carrots
directions: In a skillet, saute carrots and garlic in oil for 5 minutes. Add water, salt, thyme and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and cook for 8 to 12 minutes or until carrots are tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: pear salad
directions: In blender, combine pears and cream cheese.
Dissolve jello in 1/2 cup hot water.
Combine with pear mixture.
Mix Dream Whip (by package directions) and combine all ingredients together. Chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Salt chicken and boil until tender.
Cut into bite size pieces.
In a saucepan, melt cheese, cream of mushroom and chicken soup together.

title: avocado with gazpacho
directions: Combine onion, tomato, cucumbers, bell pepper, jalapeno pepper and lemon juice.
Brush avocado with lemon juice to keep from turning brown.
Put avocado on lettuce and put in onion mixture. Serve with chips.
Do the same with remaining ingredients and pour sauce over same.
Serves 12.

title: tri-colored pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package and drain. Add tomato, broccoli, cauliflower, cheese and cucumbers. Toss lightly. Marinate with the Italian dressing. May serve right away or refrigerate overnight.

title: super beef soup
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Lower heat to simmer for 3 to 4 hours.

title: memaw's clam chowder
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in water until tender.
Fry bacon and add to potatoes.
Chop clams and add to chowder and cook 8 to 10 minutes more.

title: perfect pot roast
directions: Prepare oven to 350°.
Heat oil in a heavy Dutch oven or casserole over medium heat.
Add meat and brown on all sides. Remove the meat and lower heat slightly.
To the pan, add onion, carrots, celery and garlic.
Cook until they begin to brown and are tender.
Add wine, stock or water, tomato paste, salt, pepper, thyme, cinnamon and bay leaf.
Drain off fat.
Return meat to the pan.
Cover and place in oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, until meat is tender.
Transfer meat to a warm platter and cover.
Strain the sauce; skim the fat from the top (using a degreasing pitcher if you have one).
Return sauce to stovetop and whisk in cornstarch. Bring to a simmer, stirring often, until it thickens.
Season with salt and pepper.
Slice the meat and pour some of the gravy over the meat.
Pass the rest.
Serves 8.

title: easy fat-free vanilla frosting
directions: In a clean glass bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar; continue beating, adding honey and vanilla.
Gradually add nonfat dry milk, beating constantly.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat until done.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese in small bowl on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Beat in yogurt and milk on low speed until well blended.
Add pudding and pie filling (dry).
Beat on medium speed for 1 to 2 minutes or until mixture mounds slightly.
Spread in pie shell.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or until set.
Top with fruit or fruit pie filling, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marie's barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and let simmer for 15 minutes.

title: old-fashioned peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Cook without stirring, until forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until it loses its gloss.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Marinate spareribs in shoyu, cornstarch, salt and sherry for 10 minutes.
Heat oil in saucepan.
Brown ginger and garlic in oil.
Brown spareribs.
Drain off excess fat. Add vinegar, brown sugar and water.
Simmer 30 minutes or until done.
Add pineapple chunks and heat through.

title: cinnamon apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mixture will be a heavy dough.
Bake at 325° in a well-greased pan (tube pan 1 hour and 45 minutes, 9 x 13-inch pan 1 hour and 10 minutes, or sheet pan 55 minutes).
Pour Hot Buttermilk Sauce over cool cake.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion chopped in it.
Drain; salt and pepper.
Cook noodles as directed on box.
Layer ground beef, diced tomatoes, noodles, sprinkle cubes of margarine, then cheese slices. Repeat layers, ending with cheese on top.
Bake in oven 35 to 40 minutes at 350°, covered.
Remove cover and brown cheese.
Serve.

title: potato casserole for 12
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add potatoes and mix well.
Place in 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Could halve it.

title: pumpkin nut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs and pumpkin. Mix well.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and spices. Add to wet ingredients.
Mix well. Add nuts and raisins.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: french chocolate candy
directions: Melt chips and stir in the next 4 ingredients.
Cool 5 minutes.
Roll into 1 or 1 1/2-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar, nuts or coconut.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, the sugars and pudding
mix
in large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in
oats and
raisins.
Drop
by
rounded
teaspoonfuls
onto ungreased baking
sheets,
about 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Make about 5 dozen.

title: kool-n-fruity pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Enjoy.

title: fruit pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding lemon juice last.
Chill thoroughly before cutting.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cranberry chiffon pudding
directions: Heat cranberry sauce to boiling, stirring constantly.
Add orange gelatin. Stir until dissolved. Add lemon juice and rind. Place over bowl with ice.
Stir until thickened and cooled.
Whip until fluffy. Fold in whipped egg white and cream. Turn into individual dessert dishes. Cover and chill about 4 hours until set.
Serve garnished with additional whipped cream.
Preparation time:
20 to 25 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Season some macaroni inside it.
Use cheese for the seasoning. Stir it up and put it on top of the oven just for a little bit long.
Put it inside a bowl.
Then you get a drink too. Then you eat.

title: microwave cheesy green beans
directions: In a medium-large covered casserole dish that is microwave-safe, combine green beans, margarine and salt and pepper (do not drain green beans).
Heat green beans for approximately 3 1/2 minutes.
Drain green beans.
Add cheese and drained mushrooms to green beans.
Heat for 2 minutes and stir.
Continue this process until cheese is melted.

title: soft rye bread sticks with caraway seed
directions: Measure warm water into a large bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt, 1 tablespoon caraway seed and softened margarine.
Stir in rye flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add enough white flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover, let rise in warm place, free from draft, until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: lumberjacks
directions: Cream the sugar and lard; add molasses and eggs, then add dry ingredients.
Have at hand a small bowl of sugar.
Dipping the fingers into the sugar, pinch off a ball of cookie dough, about the size of a walnut.
Dip the ball into sugar and arrange on cookie sheet.

title: basic cream soup(makes 3 to 4 servings)
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and celery in margarine until tender. Stir in flour.
Add milk; cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Season with salt and pepper (any desired cooked vegetables or meals can be added with milk).

title: sloppy joe casserole
directions: Mix in casserole dish; top with shredded cheese.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: brunch egg bake
directions: Combine cheeses.
Place 3 cups in an ungreased 13 X 9 X 2 inch baking dish and set aside.
In a medium skillet saute mushrooms, onions and red peppers in butter until tender.
Drain.
Place over cheese.
Top with ham.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
In a bowl beat eggs.
Add milk, flour, parsley, basil, salt and pepper, mix well.
Slowly pour over the cheese.
Bake at 350 for 35 - 40 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: tomato italian salad dressing
directions: Combine all and chill until needed.
Sometimes I add more water to have a lighter dressing.
Good on grapefruit, olive and bibb lettuce salad.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Cover beans with water.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Simmer until tender.
Add water during cooking if necessary.
Drain beans but save cooking water.
Place beans, onion, salt, pepper, molasses, dry mustard, garlic and brown sugar in Dutch oven.
Mix gently with 2 cups of bean liquid until all ingredients are blended.
Top with slices of bacon.
Cover and bake for 3 hours.

title: pastry shells
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let chill.
Gently press dough into each cup.
Press evenly over side and bottom to form a tart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: walnut pound cake
directions: Mix together sugar and oil.
Beat in eggs 2 at a time.
Add flour, milk and flavoring.
Beat 3 minutes.
Add nuts and stir. Bake at 325° until done, 1 hour and 10 minutes to 1 hour and 20 minutes.
When toothpick comes out clean, cake is done.

title: tropical fruit medley(guilt-free dessert)
directions: For sauce, in a small mixing bowl, stir together yogurt, cheese, honey and ginger until mixture is smooth; cover and chill, if desired.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the confectioners sugar, brown sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Using a wooden spoon and rubber spatula, add peanut butter (take off cap and foil, then zap in microwave for about 1 minute to soften).
Then add melted margarine (melt in microwave) and vanilla.
When mixture is well blended, spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan, using fingers to spread evenly.

title: linda's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salt water for about 6 minutes.
Stir in margarine until melted.
Mix 2 eggs, salt and pepper to taste and milk in a separate bowl.
In a baking dish, alternate layers of macaroni with shredded cheese.
Make sure macaroni and cheese are covered with the milk and egg mixture.
Bake at 400° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine ground meat, grated carrots, grated onion, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Form into balls and brown in oven.
In a large pot, combine chili sauce and cranberry sauce.
Stir over low heat until liquified.
Add browned meatballs and cover; stir occasionally.
Simmer on low for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve over cooked rice and enjoy.

title: cherry berry slush
directions: Thaw frozen fruit; do not drain.
Place raspberries in blender until smooth.
Strain and discard seeds.
Blend cherries and apple juice until smooth.
Mix with raspberries in bowl.
Freeze overnight or up to 2 months in airtight container.
When ready to serve, scrape spoon across frozen slush; place in glass.
Slowly pour 4 ounces lemon-lime over.
Stir gently to mix.
Garnish with lime.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Crush saltine crackers into crumbs.
Combine ground chuck, cracker crumbs, chopped onion, egg and pepper together.
Mix together well and form patties (children like "meatball" shape). Brown in skillet or microwave to cook outside.
Mix and cook gravy as directed on package.
Pour gravy (and mushrooms, if desired,) over patties in Dutch oven type pot.
Simmer gravy and patties over low heat about 40 minutes.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: date nut candy
directions: Mix sugar,
butter
and milk.
Cook to soft ball stage. Add chopped dates and cook about 5 minutes longer.

title: louise's cream nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cook in 2 (9-inch) pans.

title: beef jerky
directions: Mix well.
Pour over meat.
Marinate over night. Put in dehydrator or 100 degree oven draped over bamboo skewers.
Leave oven door open.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 11-inch pan.
Dump undrained pineapple in pan; spread evenly.
Dump pie filling on top and spread evenly.
Dump dry cake mix on cherry layer and spread evenly.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Put slices of margarine on top.
Bake 48 to 53 minutes.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook in crock-pot all day.
Start on high for 2 hours.
Turn to low for as long as you want.
Stir occasionally.

title: spanish meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, oats, onion flakes, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Shape into balls; place in baking pan.
Combine in bowl, ketchup, vinegar, water and sugar.
Mix well.
Pour over meatballs. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Let cool about 20 minutes; then peel off skins.
Dice potatoes in bowl.
Chop hard-boiled eggs and add to potatoes.
Add rest of ingredients and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Coarsely shred potatoes, zucchini and carrots. Drain and pat dry. Place 1/2 of veggies and 1/4 cup of onions in a blender or food processor. Cover and process until finely chopped. Transfer to a bowl and add eggs, flour, garlic, salt, sugar and dried basil. Add remaining onion and vegetables; mix well. In a large skillet, heat oil and drop potato mixture by tablespoons; flatten to form patties. Fry until golden brown. Turn over gently and brown other side.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs until smooth.
Add flour and 7-Up alternately.
Add flavoring.
Bake in 275° oven until done, 1 hour and 10 to 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, bananas and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add flour and baking soda.
Blend well; stir in nuts.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes; test with a toothpick inserted in center.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Loosen sides with a knife and turn out onto a wire rack or serving plate to cool.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend together cream cheese, butter and sugar with electric mixer on medium speed.
With mixer on low speed, blend in eggs.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to cheese mixture and blend until smooth.
Pour into buttered and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake for 80
minutes, until golden brown.
Sprinkle cake with powdered sugar after it has cooled. Serves 12.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and salt, and fold in remaining ingredients, except poppy seed and anise.
Bake in prepared metal loaf pan 45 minutes at 350° (glass 325°).
Sprinkle poppy seed and anise on batter before baking if desired.

title: stewed cabbage
directions: Cook ground beef until done; drain.
In a big pot, put ground beef in with other ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then, over a medium heat, let it simmer for 1 hour or until vegetables are done.
Serve hot over mashed potatoes.
Season to taste.

title: stir-fry turkey and green beans
directions: Remove bone from turkey breast and slice meat into thin, bite sized strips.
(Will slice easier if slightly frozen.)
Combine soy sauce, onion, garlic, ginger and sesame seed; let turkey marinate as long as is convenient (15 minutes or overnight). Stir-fry turkey in oil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add green beans and additional sauce (2 tablespoons), if desired.
Cover and simmer 12 to 15 minutes or until green beans are desired tenderness.
Serves 6.
Serve with rice.

title: chocolate covered peanut pie
directions: In a bowl, combine ice cream, whipped topping, peanut butter and 2/3 cup chopped peanuts; mix thoroughly.
Spoon into baked pie shell.
Top with remaining peanuts and drizzle with chocolate topping.
Freeze until firm, several hours or overnight.
Allow to defrost 15 to 20 minutes before slicing.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Do not beat as you mix together; use a spoon.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese; mix all ingredients except 1 cup of pecans. Chill.
Form into a ball and roll in other cup of pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: maple-glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water, covered, 20 minutes or just until tender.
Drain.
Prepare glaze.
Melt butter in large heavy skillet.
Add sugar and syrup.
Simmer, uncovered, 8 to 10 minutes or until thick and syrupy.
When carrots are done dump into skillet; toss until glossy.
Keep warm.
Serves 10.

title: old-fashioned baked beans
directions: Wash beans.
Add water, cover and heat to boiling.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Drain; keep liquid.
Place onion on bottom of bean pot or 10-cup casserole.
Combine next 7 ingredients and put into bean pot.
Add the beans and enough hot liquid or water to cover. Arrange meat on top, cover and bake at 250° for 7 to 8 hours.

title: cheesy chicken and macaroni casserole
directions: Follow directions on macaroni and cheese.
When ready, add soup and chicken.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste

title: pot roast
directions: Rub salt and pepper well onto roast.
Brown on 4 sides in small amount of oil.
Dice onion and garlic and cook until onion is clear.
Mix vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and enough water to make 1 cup.
Add to roast with another cup of water.
Cover tightly and cook until tender.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix well and keep in jar and refrigerate.

title: quick and zesty vegetable soup
directions: In large pot, brown meat with onion and drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes or until noodles and vegetables are done.
Preparation time:
5 minutes.
Cook time:
20 minutes.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Put ingredients in blender and mix until creamy.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of 2 loaf pans.
Mix bananas, milk, cereal and vanilla with spoon in small bowl.
Let stand about 5 minutes or until cereal is softened.
Mix sugar and margarine in large bowl; stir in eggs until well blended.
Beat in banana mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour in pans. Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before slicing.

title: beef chow mein
directions: Brown meat; add celery and onion.
Add soups, water and other ingredients.
Heat to slow boil.
Pour into greased casserole pan. Preheat oven to 350° and cook for about 1 hour.
Stir casserole during baking so rice does not remain on bottom.

title: "icebox" cake
directions: Mix and cook puddings as directed on box (separately).
Line the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish with graham crackers. Pour enough chocolate pudding on top of graham crackers to cover crackers.
Place a layer of graham crackers covering chocolate pudding.
Pour enough vanilla pudding on top of graham crackers to cover crackers.
Continue layers of crackers, chocolate pudding and vanilla pudding (last layer should be vanilla pudding).
Crush a few crackers and sprinkle on top of last layer of pudding. Place in refrigerator until firm (2 to 3 hours).

title: mexican chicken
directions: Use broth from chicken to make sauce a little runny.
Tear up tortillas and mix all ingredients together in casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: meatballs or meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind
vegetables,
then boil together 25 minutes, then add 1 small
can mustard, 1 cup flour, 1 teaspoon turmeric and 1 pint weak vinegar.
Cook
minutes
longer with the other stuff. Put in jars and seal.

title: never fail peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until mixture will spin a thread. Add peanuts.
Cook about 10 minutes, stirring constantly, until mixture turns a brownish gold.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and soda.
Stir just enough to mix well.

title: blueberry rainbow salad
directions: Slice 2 large strawberries and reserve.
Combine whole strawberries and 1/2 of the blueberries; spoon into glass serving dish.
Layer melon balls on top of strawberry mixture.
Top with remaining blueberries.
Blend orange juice, lemon juice, sugar and chopped mint in a small bowl; pour over fruit.
Arrange kiwi and sliced strawberries on top.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish with grapes and mint sprigs, if desired.
Serves 12.

title: butter bean casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Add tomato sauce, sugar, seasoning, onion and 1/2 to 1 cup juice from the beans.
Drain beans; put in casserole dish.
Add sausage ingredients; cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jibloks casserole(eggplant)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crackers and margarine.
Toss. Take out and reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
Add remaining ingredients to crumbs.
Turn into greased casserole and top with reserved crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: paradise pie
directions: Mix crackers, egg whites, vanilla, sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cool!
Whip cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Set aside.
Whip Dream Whip as directed on package. Mix with cream cheese the crushed pineapple.
Top with nuts and let set overnight.

title: chocolate-chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine dry cake mix and dry chocolate instant pudding mix together.
Mix sour cream, oil, sugar, eggs and milk together. Fold in dry mix.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased and floured Bundt cake pan.

title: idaho potato cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in potatoes and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda; add alternately with milk, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.

title: crock-pot beef stroganoff
directions: Combine the three soups and mushrooms in crock-pot.
Add uncooked meat.
Cook on medium to high for 8 to 10 hours, depending on desired tenderness.
Thicken if needed.
Serve over rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: broccoli lasagna
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, heat the undiluted broccoli soup and frozen broccoli
until
the broccoli is completely thawed. Set aside.
In a
small
skillet,
heat 1 tablespoon oil until hot and cook
carrots
and onion until slightly brown.
Reduce heat to low and stir
in
cup water.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Remove from skillet; set aside.
Add rest of the oil to same skillet.
Over high heat, cook mushrooms until slightly brown and all
liquid
is gone; stir in the carrot mixture. Remove
from heat.
Cook
the
lasagna
noodles
according
to package directions;
drain.
Meanwhile,
mix
Mozzarella, Ricotta, eggs and black pepper together.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Drain fat. Stir in canned spaghetti. Heat until bubbly. Flatten in skillet and top with cheese slices.
Reduce heat and allow cheese to soften before serving.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender; bone chicken and tear into bite size pieces.
Put into large baking dish.
Melt margarine.
Add sweet milk, pepper, salt and margarine to broth; bring to a boil. Pour over chicken.
Make batter of flour, buttermilk and oil; pour over top of pie.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until top is brown.

title: german gold poundcake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan or two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Into large bowl measure sugar and butter; with mixer at high speed, beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour and rest of ingredients; at low speed, beat until well mixed, constantly scraping the bowl with a rubber spatula.
Beat at high speed for 4 minutes, occasionally scraping the bowl.
Pour batter into pan and bake in Bundt pan 1 hour or in loaf pans for 45 to 50 minutes (until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean).
Cool cake in pan on wire rack 10 minutes; remove from pan; cool on rack.
(Ice it if so desired.)

title: apple delight
directions: Slice apples into a 2-quart baking dish.
Pour granulated sugar over apples.
Mix melted margarine, flour, brown sugar and nuts. Distribute evenly over apples. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Do not bake longer or topping will be too hard.
Delicious served warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: liz's oatmeal cookies(club member: ben steadman)
directions: Beat eggs; keep separate.
Mix 2 sugars, oats, flour, baking soda and salt.
Add cooking oil, eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and nuts. Stir together well.
Spoon into 1-inch rounds onto baking sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 325°.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Beat egg white until frothy.
Add water.
Beat until soft peaks form.
Stir in pecans until coated.
Toss gently.

title: almond punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sugar to dissolve.
Add rest of ingredients.
The longer this is in the refrigerator, the more the flavors blend.
You can use extra Kool-Aid dissolved in the amount of water called for to stretch this punch.

title: swiss steak
directions: Coat steak with flour.
Brown quickly in hot oil, now add chopped vegetables to steak.
Add salt and pepper; now cover with tomatoes.
Cover and cook at medium heat for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Mix and bake cake according to directions, using juice instead of water.
When cake is done, slice into four layers.
Fill with filling made of crushed pineapple, one box of vanilla instant pudding and whipped cream.

title: hawaiian stuffed chicken(2 grams fat each)
directions: Mix hot water and butter buds in bowl.
Stir in stuffing mix, pepper and half of pineapple and syrup.
Spoon stuffing mix evenly over chicken.
Roll tightly.
Secure with toothpicks.
Place in square baking dish, place any leftover stuffing in the middle. Mix remaining pineapple, syrup, sugar, vinegar and ginger.
Spoon over chicken rolls.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy bean burrito bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch glass pie plate. Cook ground beef with diced onion until browned; drain. Add taco seasoning.
Mix beans, baking mix and water. Spread in bottom and halfway up side of pie plate.
Top with beef, chillies, salsa and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes. Top each serving with chopped lettuce, chopped tomatoes and a dollop of sour cream.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine milk, sugar, Crisco and salt. Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup of flour and beat well.
Beat in softened yeast and egg.
Gradually add remaining flour to form soft dough.
Cover and let rise until double (1 1/2 hours).
Turn out on lightly floured surface and punch down.
Divide in half. In 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, mix 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/4 cup butter and 1 tablespoon corn syrup, stirring slowly.
Roll 1/2 of dough into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Brush with 3 tablespoons of soft butter. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.

title: calla lillies
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, flour and baking powder, sifting all together and add cold water.
Beat for 5 minutes. Drop by tablespoon and bake about 8 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate root beer float
directions: In 12-ounce glass, stir together sugar and cocoa.
Add water. Stir.
Add ice cream; fill glass with root beer.
Stir.
Serve immediately.
Yields one (12 ounce) serving.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix and pour over oyster crackers.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes.

title: a pie for grandma
directions: Lightly beat milk and pudding mix until smooth.
Add Cool Whip and mix easy until smooth.
Spread in graham crust and chill.
You can use lite cream cheese and Cool Whip to cut calories.

title: hawaiian rice salad
directions: Fold together with one package of Dream Whip.
Chill, then serve.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Boil whole cauliflower in salted water until just under cooked, about 15 minutes.

title: executive potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
Chill.
When cool, peel and grate into casserole dish.
Combine 1/4 cup butter, cheese, chives, salt, pepper and sour cream.
Blend well; pour over potatoes. Stir gently.
Dot top with 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Shred the cabbage.
Place in a saucepan with salt and water. Boil 3 to 5 minutes; do not overcook.
Drain well.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add the cabbage and stir until well blended. Deep fry by tablespoonfuls in hot oil.
Serves 10.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Into an 8 x 8-inch glass pan, layer in the following ingredients:

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook shrimp and place in a casserole.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and oil; refrigerate.
Cook rice and chill.
Saute pepper and onion in butter; add to rice and shrimp.
Add salt and all the rest of the ingredients except almonds and paprika.
Stir well. Top with almonds and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: low calorie strawberry shake
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In a cup combine yeast with warm water.
In a pot, scald milk. Blend in sugar until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat.
Let stand until warm.
Blend egg and yeast.
In a large bowl, combine yeast mixture with flour and cinnamon.
Blend butter.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Combine rice, soup, chicken gravy and chicken.
Put into 2-quart casserole.
Toss together bread crumbs and melted butter. Sprinkle over top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add blueberries and set aside. Beat milk, oil and egg with fork. Make a hole in the center of the flour mixture; add milk mixture all at once. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly brown on top.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Cut off ends and slice pickles thinly crosswise.
Mix sugar, vinegar and grated onion together.
Add pickles and leave uncovered on cabinet overnight.
Put in jars.
Will keep well in refrigerator.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drizzle into hot oil.
Turn when brown (about 1/2 minute).
Brown other side.
Top with powdered sugar. (Use iron skillet.)

title: fried apples
directions: Peel and slice apples into slices.
Melt butter in skillet and add apples and sugar.
Fry on medium-high for approximately 30 minutes or until thick.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Cut up and fry bacon; drain.
Add to beans which can be put in a crock-pot or some other kettle.
Fry onion and hamburg.
If greasy, drain and add to bean mixture.
Add brown sugar and ketchup.
Cook slowly.

title: cajun corn casserole
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in 13 x 9-inch or 11 x 9-inch pan. Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes or saute on stove.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scallops and bacon
directions: Wrap each scallop with 1/2 slice bacon.
Secure with toothpick. Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes, turning and draining frequently, until bacon is crisp.

title: nutritious oatmeal cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl combine brown sugar, eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir into batter.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and raisins. Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove immediately.
Yields 3 1/2 or 4 dozen.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins in water until tender, then mix sugar, cornstarch, milk and egg yolks. Add to the cooled raisins.
Cook until thick. Add 2 tablespoons margarine. Pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue; brown.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Roll into balls and drop and roll in the cinnamon and sugar mixture, spoonful size.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Place spoonful of mixture in center of flour tortillas with a strip of American cheese.
Roll up and place in uncovered pan. Put remaining 1/2 can of cream of chicken soup over tortillas and cheese slices on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon lush dessert
directions: Combine and press into a flat cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: chicken or tuna and fruit salad
directions: Combine the fruits and chicken and rice; add 1/2 cup mayonnaise, thinned with 1 tablespoon vinegar.

title: diabetic chocolate cake
directions: Cook at 350° for 25 minutes in a greased 8-inch pan.

title: teddy's favorite play dough
directions: Cook 3 minutes to the consistency of mashed potatoes.
Turn out on waxed paper to cool.
Knead a bit.
Store in a plastic bag or other airtight container.
The cream of tartar gives this mixture a "bounce!"

title: cherry-o cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature; whip until fluffy.
Gradually add milk, while continuing to beat until well blended.
Add lemon juice and vanilla; blend well.
Pour into prepared crust and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Top with pie filling.
May be cut, then topped with cherry, blueberry or strawberry pie filling.
May be kept in crumb tart shells.

title: papa george's birthday muffins
directions: Mix applesauce, honey and eggs in bowl.
In a second bowl, whisk together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients to honey mixture.
Blend together and add crushed pineapple and juice, mixing until well blended.
Add vanilla, pecans and raisins.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen muffins.

title: cheeseburger cookies
directions: Spread yellow frosting on one wafer and red frosting on another wafer.
Put chocolate mint cookie in the middle and press together so frosting squishes out side a little.
Roll in green coconut lightly.
Rub a little sugar water on top and sprinkle with 5 or 6 sesame seeds.
Serve with shoestring potatoes.

title: breathren cheese bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in large bowl.
Cut butter in until coarse crumbs result.
Stir in cheese, onion and dill weed.
Mix well.
Combine milk and beaten eggs.
Pour into flour mixture all at once.
Stir quickly with fork to moisten flour.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan before serving. Serve warm.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Drain; save juice.
Slice the banana; cover with the juice.
Whip the heavy cream.
Add the mayonnaise.
Drain banana.
Fold lightly the fruits into the cream and mayonnaise.
Pour into pan.
Cover.
Freeze for 5 or 6 hours. Cut into slices; serve on lettuce.

title: quick pickle cucumber salad
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar.
Set aside to cool.
Slice cucumbers and cover with salt.
Let set at least 1 hour.
Wash cucumbers well.
Mix with sliced onions.
Add other ingredients.
Stir. Cover and refrigerate.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Melt first 2 ingredients together over low heat; mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Grate sharp Cheddar cheese over top generously.
Onion may also be added.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: beef with cashews(chinese)
directions: Cut beef across grain into thin slices about 2 inches long. Heat 2 tablespoons vegetable oil in large skillet over high heat. Stir-fry 1/2 of the beef until brown; 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
Repeat with remaining beef.
Combine water, cornstarch, soy sauce, sesame oil, oyster sauce and chili sauce in small bowl; mix well.
Heat remaining 2 tablespoons vegetable oil in pan over high heat.
Add onions, garlic, ginger and cashews.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Add meat and cornstarch mixture.
Cook and stir until liquid boils and thickens.

title: dirty, dirty rice
directions: Mix ground meat with rice. Add onion, bell pepper, celery, onion and parsley.
Mix in the soups and season with red and black pepper.
Put into a heavy casserole dish and cover with close fitting cover in order to retain the juice.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, rice, chestnuts, onion and celery. Combine soups and mayonnaise and mix well with Veg-All. Pour into baking dish. Top with buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° until browned on top.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: Cook eggs, vinegar and sugar, stirring until thick.
Add butter.
Cool.
Fold in cream.
Fold in fruits.
Let stand covered in refrigerator 2 hours, stirring several times.

title: curried chicken
directions: Saute apple and onion in margarine (or butter).
Add curry powder, soup and half and half, mix well.
Put chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish in one layer.
Pour on sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes whole or peel and slice (cut up).
Cook until done.
Drain water off and blend together while hot.
Add margarine, sugar, milk, egg and flour.
Blend well and pour into pie shell and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add the remaining ingredients; mix by hand only.
Pour into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: golden shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onions in
oleo
in
medium saucepan.
Add soups, shrimp, pimentos, rice,
onion tops and parsley.
Mix well and season to taste.
Pour in
baking dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
More rice may be added when removed from oven.

title: champagne punch
directions: Allow frozen apple juice to thaw to slush consistency and mix in punch bowl with remaining chilled ingredients.

title: crescent roll party bites
directions: Spread rolls out to cover bottom of an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Spread with cream cheese, mayo and Hidden Valley Ranch dry mix.
Beat well and put on top of crescent layer.
Chop broccoli, carrots and green pepper fine with processor or blender.
Put on top of cream cheese mixture.
Then grate cheeses and put on top of vegetables.
Put in warm oven until cheese melts.
Cut in bite size serving pieces.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss broccoli, green onions, grated cheese and bacon together lightly.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; top salad.

title: lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a blender container combine all ingredients except coconut.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie plate.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut over top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Let cool before serving.

title: creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine these items and pour into a 10-inch pie pan. When knife comes out clean like custard, it will be done. Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Add 1 can Hormel chili with beans, then add meat.
Serve warm over Doritos.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse all beans.
Add the rest of the ingredients and stir well.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours before serving.

title: blue cheese burgers
directions: Cook onion in heated butter in a large heavy frying pan until lightly browned.
Remove from heat.
Set aside.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Cook noodles according to package and drain.
Cut cheese into small chunks. Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: morning rice
directions: Mix ingredients together. Jam could be used in place of honey, or on fruit if you like.
Serves 2.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put broccoli, raisins, chopped onion and bacon in bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar and add to ingredients and mix well. Chill 2 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, setting aside 3/4 cup cheese. Pour mixture into a greased casserole dish and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Can be made 1 to 2 days ahead.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Batter will be sticky. Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake!
To make very large cookies, use ice cream scoop and place about 6 scoops on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
I usually opt for using heaping tablespoons.
The secret is not to overbake!

title: touchdown chili
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and cook until translucent.
Add hamburger, chili powder, oregano, cumin and garlic.
Break up hamburger with a fork.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until evenly browned.
Stir in tomato soup, onion soup and kidney beans.
Bring to a boil and then lower heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until liquid cooks down and mixture thickens.

title: ruth's cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients and whisk until moist.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 50 minutes or until done.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onion, parsley flakes, pepper and bouillon granules in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with lid. Microwave (High) for 8 to 10 minutes, until vegetables are tender, stirring once.
Add 1/4 cup milk to the flour and stir until smooth.
Stir flour mixture, remaining milk and butter into potato mixture.
Microwave (High), uncovered, for 8 to 10 minutes, until thickened, stirring frequently during cooking.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 2 buttered loaf pans in 325° oven, 1 1/2 hours until browned.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients and cook until thick.
Pour into casserole dish.

title: peach dessert
directions: Pour sliced peaches in bottom of glass casserole dish. Cut them into smaller pieces (bite size). Sprinkle dry cake mix over peaches. Pour melted butter over cake mix. You can add chopped pecans to top of dessert. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugars together.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour, baking soda, salt, vanilla and oats.
Stir well.
Add coconut, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, salt, pepper and celery seed in a small amount of water until done. Add milk and bring to a boil. Add butter. Make a thickening of 3 tablespoons of flour and a little water. Add thickening to soup and cook a few more minutes, until soup thickens.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; add eggs and oil; stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove.
Cool completely.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: corn and tomato bisque
directions: In soup pot cook onion, bell pepper and garlic in butter until soft. Add milk, tomatoes, herbs, salt and pepper. Cover and bring to gentle boil, lower heat and simmer 1 minute.
