Discard bay leaf. Add corn kernels, reheat and season with salt to taste. Garnish with parsley and pass the croutons.

title: nutty-topped tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush tomato skins with oil.
Place, cut side up, in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in medium bowl, spoon mixture onto tomatoes.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Store in airtight container.
Stir 6 tablespoons of mix into 3/4 cup hot water.
This mix gives a much richer flavor than the instant cocoa on the market and is very convenient to keep on hand and use as needed.
Makes 15 servings.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops. Put in bottom of casserole dish. Slice potatoes. Put on top of pork chops. Add cream of mushroom. Spread soup over potatoes. Add 3/4 cup of water. Cook at 350° for 2 hours.

title: garden harvest chowder
directions: Fry bacon in a large saucepan until crisp; drain on paper towels. Crumble bacon. Reserve 1 Tbsp. drippings in pan. Saute onion, celery, and carrot in reserved drippings for 2 minutes. Stir in potatoes, corn, peas, milk, salt, and cheese. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until cheese melts. Top each serving with a tomato slice, bacon and a dash of seasoned pepper.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown, crumble and drain sausage and set aside. In covered saucepan, cook soup mix, rice and water for 7 minutes. Then combine all ingredients and place in baking dish (may be prepared day before needed). Bake 1 hour in 350° oven; serves 8 to 10. Good served with mushroom gravy.

title: quick and easy chicken soup
directions: Mix chicken, soup, liquid and spices.
Bring to boil.
Pour in noodles and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers or toast.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger (mixed with onion and pepper).
Drain.
In crock-pot, or on top of stove, in large kettle, combine meat mixture with rest of ingredients and simmer for as long as you like. (The longer you simmer, the more flavorful.)
Pour over favorite pasta.

title: one pan banana bread
directions: Mix all the above and pour into bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.

title: secret barbecue sauce(not so secret anymore)
directions: Combine all ingredients and brush on chicken or ribs.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Add milk and beaten eggs. Cook until thick.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and add meringue.
Bake until lightly browned at 350°.

title: rosie's no fat fries
directions: Slice potatoes into strips.
Pat dry.
Toss potato strips with egg whites and seasoning.
Bake on a large cookie sheet, sprayed generously with Pam, for 25 minutes at 400°.
Important to turn every 5 minutes.
This is what crisps the fries.
Serves 4.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cream together the oleo, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Beat for about 20 minutes total.
Add sifted flour and lemon extract.
Fold in 7-Up.
Bake in greased and floured deep tube or Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: banana chocolate chip muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix Miracle Whip and sugar.
Add bananas, combine flour, baking soda and chips; mix until moist.
Spoon batter into muffin pan, filling each cup 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place both cups sugar and milk into a saucepan.
Bring just to a boil, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla flavoring and peanut butter.
Beat with electric mixer for 5 minutes.
It is ready when the candy begins to stick to sides of pan.
Pour onto a buttered platter and let harden at room temperature.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: old fashioned carrot cake
directions: Sift flour and dry ingredients together. Add oil and eggs. Mix well.
Add pineapple (except for 2 tablespoons) and carrots. Add nuts.
Bake in three 9-inch pans. Grease and flour.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 3 bean chili
directions: Brown 2 hamburger patties and drain grease.
Put all ingredients in a crock pot with juices from the cans.
Stir ingredients and cook 8 - 12 hours.	Stir every 3 to 4 hours. Serve with graded multi variety Mexican style cheese over top of chili. Excellent with cornbread or served over fritos.
Serves 15-20.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot chocolate syrup
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add milk and butter.
Microwave; bring to a boil and let boil until you reach desired thickness.
Add vanilla.
If it is too thick, just add milk.
To reheat, add milk.

title: mexican turkey casserole (microwave)(freda adams, bethel, ohio)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine turkey, gravy, sour cream, chili peppers, green onions and olives.
Grease the sides of a microwave-safe 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle 1/3 of the corn chips over the bottom of casserole.
Pour half the turkey mixture over chips.
Top with half the cheese.
Repeat layers, reserving last portion of corn chips.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Layer all ingredients as follows:
beans, picante sauce, sour cream, cheese, olives and onions in 3-quart shallow dish.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sweet cinnamon biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease baking pan.
Combine flour, salt, and baking soda and mix well.
Stir in vegetable oil and mix, then add buttermilk and mix.
Knead dough and roll out in a rectangle.
Spread butter over dough.
In bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over butter.
Roll dough in jelly roll fashion, starting from one long side, pinch seam sealed.
Cut into slices and bake until brown (approximately 15-20 minutes).
Serve hot.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini 5 minutes and drain.
Mix butter with half of the bread crumbs, then mix with other ingredients.
The other half of the bread crumbs go on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup may be used.

title: cavatini
directions: Dice up pepper and onion.
Cook with hamburger meat.
When done, drain.
Add cooked noodles, Pizza Quick, cheese and pepperoni.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: zesty lasagne
directions: Mix ground beef, onion and black pepper, then brown and drain off grease.
Add your red pepper, Texas Pete, tomato sauce, tomato paste, spaghetti mix and Texas red chili and simmer about 20 minutes.
Then cook noodles until done.
Then take out your baking dish and lay a row of noodles, then your sauce, then sprinkle both types of cheese and repeat.
Then bake for about 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy blender chocolate mousse
directions: Place the chocolate bits in blender and pour the very hot coffee over the bits. Cover blender and run on high speed for 10 seconds (or until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth).
Add egg yolks and vanilla. Cover again and blend on high speed for 5 seconds more.

title: kraut salad
directions: Pour hot water over kraut; drain and cool.
Add onion, peppers, celery and pimento.
Heat sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture and marinate overnight.

title: nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add milk and flavoring.
Add flour, saving 1/2 cup of flour to dredge nuts in.
Add nuts last.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: grandma jewell's chicken pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add mushrooms and garlic.
Combine cornstarch and milk.
When smooth, add to mushroom mixture.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Pour into pastry shells.
Cover pie with pastry.
Seal and flute edges. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and let set until it begins to thicken.
Crush crackers; mix it with oleo and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan, saving about 1/3 cup for topping.

title: pecan butter ball cookies(makes 4 dozen cookies)
directions: Cream butter.
Add the 1/2 cup powdered sugar, the salt and vanilla as you keep beating.
Beat until very light.
Stir in flour slowly.
Add nuts.
Chill.
Shape into one-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Roll hot cookies in the reserved powdered sugar.
Cool and then reroll in the sugar.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and margarine. Add eggs and pecans. Fill unbaked pie crust with mixture and bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chinese beef and hot tomato stir-fry
directions: Cut beef against the grain in 1/4-inch slices, then in 1 1/2 to 2-inch strips.
Quarter tomatoes.
Cut scallion stalks in 1-inch sections.
Heat oil.
Add salt if desired, then scallions and stir-fry until it loses redness.
Stir in stock and heat quickly.
Cook, covered, 1 to 2 minutes over medium heat.

title: ham glaze
directions: Blend on high speed and simmer for 10 minutes.
Baste every 15 minutes during the last 45 minutes of baking ham.

title: apple omelet(serves 4 to 6)
directions: This is a very delicate dish to serve with broiled spareribs or roast pork.
Cook the apples until very soft, then mash them and add butter or margarine, sugar, eggs and spice.
Bake (250° to 350°) in a shallow pudding dish or pie tin until brown.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Keep corn hot and crisp in a slow 300° oven.
Combine rest of ingredients and cook to hard ball stage (270°).
Pour slowly over popcorn. Mix well and shape into balls using butter on hands. Makes 15 to 20 balls.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Melt butter in pan; set aside.
Beat egg yolks with water and lemon juice.
Cook in double boiler until mixture is thick. Slowly add melted butter to egg mixture, beating constantly.
Use immediately.

title: lemon-sour cream-poppy seed muffins
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Mix cake mix (dry) with remaining ingredients in large bowl until well blended.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full. Bake 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, remove from pan.
Spread with lemon glaze.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: birdfeed snack
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl, mix well.
Store covered until serving time.

title: grilled tossed vegetables
directions: Peel and cube eggplant to make 6 cups.
Mix with the chopped green pepper and chopped onion.
Cut 3 pieces of heavy-duty foil about 12 x 18-inches.
Divide the eggplant mixture evenly on foil. Place 1 teaspoon margarine on mixture; sprinkle with basil or if preferred use chopped fresh basil.
Close foil tightly.
Place foil packs on grill 3 to 4 inches from heat.
Cook for about 35 minutes. Chop tomato and place on another piece of foil.
Close foil and place on grill the last 15 minutes of eggplant cooking time. Remove vegetables from foil; blend together in large bowl.
Season to taste with salt and black pepper.
Yield:
4 servings. Carbohydrate 11 g, protein 2 g, fat 3.3 g, calories 75.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add refried beans and salsa. Line 9 x 13-inch baking dish with tortilla chips.
Pour in beef, beans and salsa mixture, top with cheese and broken up tortilla chips.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: meat loaf (st.  croix, vi)
directions: Make sauce of mustard, water, tomato sauce, vinegar, sugar and juice from pineapple.
Top loaf with pineapple rings.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Mix together
all
ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Chill,
and
serve in a chilled honeydew or cantaloupe half.

title: pressed cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
You may add food coloring if you desire. I divide dough and mix different colors.
Nice for holidays. Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Beat with an eggbeater and store in refrigerator in covered container.
If it separates, just let it stand for a while at room temperature.
Always shake well before using.

title: mrs. russell's icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and then stir in milk gradually. Put in mold and let remain overnight in refrigerator.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: authentic homemade picante
directions: Use only fresh vegetables, not canned or frozen.
Dice all vegetables and place in a large bowl.
Add tomato paste, beer, lemon, salt and garlic.
Refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips or as relish on eggs, vegetables, etc.

title: sheila's old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo, white and powdered sugar.
Add eggs, salt, oil and vanilla.
Mix. Add all dry ingredients:
flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Mix well.
It will be a moist batter.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
This is not a good batter to roll out.
Place teaspoonfuls of batter on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Use a glass with a flat bottom to flatten balls.
Place glass in bowl of sugar between each flattening.
Bake at 350° to 400° until golden brown at edges.
Do not overbake.
Makes 5 dozen.
A favorite family cookie.

title: sugar cured meat
directions: To each piece of meat mix all ingredients.

title: crab and vegetable quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute sliced zucchini and mushrooms in butter.
In a big bowl combine milk, dry mustard, crabmeat, Cheddar cheese, onion powder and beaten eggs.
Mix together; add vegetables and mix.
Pour into pie plate.
Cook for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: white oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream butter and gradually add sugar; cream well and add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well and add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well and stir in oatmeal, raisins and nuts (optional).
Chill dough.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening, beaten eggs and vanilla. Add soda (put into buttermilk) and salt.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add to mixture.
Mix well.
Dough will be soft. Add enough flour that it doesn't stick when rolled.
Cut in desired shapes with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: chocolate chip sour cream cake
directions: Mix everything but chips.
Add chips last.
Use greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: Crumble and brown sausage.
Drain and cool.
In a bowl, mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Add cubed bread and stir.
Add cheese and sausage.
Refrigerate in a 9 x 13-inch pan overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetarian spaghetti
directions: Place fish fillets on aluminum foil.
Butter fish.
Sprinkle with Italian seasoning.
Wrap in foil.
Grill for approximately 30 minutes.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Gradually add the sugar and beat well.
Stir in the half and half and peaches.
(Put peaches through blender to make puree.) Add vanilla extract and milk. Pour into ice cream freezer.
Strawberries or other fruit may be substituted. Yields 1 gallon.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine ground pork, veal, bread, eggs, onion, parsley and salt.
Make tiny meatballs; brown well in margarine.
Combine preserves with barbecue sauce; pour over meatballs.
Cover dish; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix oil, sugar and vinegar for dressing.
Mix vegetables to sauerkraut and add dressing.
Chill and cover for several hours. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat all of the ingredients with mixer.
Pour into buttered baking dish.

title: lobster fra diavolo(my personal favorite)
directions: Wash
and
clean
lobster.
Remove
stomach
sack
and reserve tomally, if
desired.
In large saucepan, heat oil and saute garlic and onion until tender but not brown.
Add tomato sauce and
tomatoes;
stir
well, squashing tomatoes slightly. Add the rest of
the ingredients and cook for 20 minutes.
Add lobster to cooking
sauce
and
cook an additional 30 minutes. Serve over linguine,
cooked according to package directions. Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on the box; bake.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and ice cream topping.
Using a straw, poke holes through cake.
Pour the mixture of Eagle Brand milk and ice cream topping over the cake.
Spread the Cool Whip on top of the cake. Grate the candy bar on top of the Cool Whip.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Blend together dry ingredients well.
Whisk together eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients; mix well.
Add fruit, carrots and nuts.
Spoon batter into cupcake tins, lined with paper cups.
Fill to brim.
Bake at 350° until done.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Allow 24 hours before serving.
Delicious with cream cheese and honey.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart casserole combine all ingredients except cheese, mix well.
Bake covered at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until macaroni is tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in cheese; cover until cheese melts.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: creamy green beans
directions: Drain liquid from beans, reserving 1/2 cup.
Mix liquid with soup.
Arrange beans in casserole.
Pour soup over beans.
Cover and bake in 425° oven about 45 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add elbows, celery, pepper and onion; toss to coat well.
Cover; chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: hot crab meat spread
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix all ingredients together.
Place in a shallow 9 x 9-inch baking pan or a 1-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly and light brown, about 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers or toast.

title: old fashion walnut cake
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Bake in two round pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: super simple chili supper
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Add chili mix and stir to coat meat.
Add tomatoes and 1/2 can water.
Stir and cook for 20 minutes over low flame.
Add to cooked macaroni and heat until warm.

title: orange poppy seed dip
directions: In medium bowl combine all ingredients.
Blend well.
Cover. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups of dip.

title: deviled dip
directions: With electric mixer, thoroughly combine cheese spread, deviled ham, mayonnaise, parsley, onion and seasonings.
Chill.
Makes about 1 1/3 cups.
Serve with assorted crackers and potato chips.

title: mock chow mein
directions: Brown the first three ingredients.
Butter a casserole dish and add rice.
Set aside.
Add a can of cream of chicken (or mushroom) soup and two soup cans water.
Add four tablespoons of soy sauce. Place in casserole dish, cover and bake for one hour at 350°.
Uncover and add a can of chow mein noodles and cook 30 more minutes uncovered.
This is a great dish to cook ahead.

title: fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and oleo to 243°.
Add chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Stir well.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered pan to cool.
Cut into squares.

title: wild rice mingle
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix ingredients ahead of time. Pour over 1 bag fresh spinach. Add 1 pound of bacon, fried and crumbled. Add fresh sliced mushrooms when ready to serve.

title: family meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in large oven cooking bag and place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine meat, bread crumbs, soup mix, eggs, ketchup, salt, pepper and dry mustard. Mix until blended and shape.
Place in bag.
Place vegetables in bag around meat loaf.
Close bag with nylon tie; make 6 half-inch slits in top.
Cook 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until meat loaf is done and vegetables are tender.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and egg.
Add mashed bananas and blend well.
Last add baking soda, flour and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill.
Nuts and marshmallows can be added if desired.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Place pecan halves in a shallow baking pan in 200° oven. When pecans take on a shiny appearance, add melted butter.
Stir to coat pecans and sprinkle with salt while stirring.
Place pecans back in oven for at least 2 hours.
Recipe may be halved.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix pasta, green pepper, cucumber, onion, tomato, dressing, Salad Supreme seasoning, pepperoni and celery.
Let set overnight or at least several hours before serving.
Mix well again before serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix milk and all ingredients except vanilla and oleo.
Cook over low to medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour in vanilla and put in oleo.
Stir until melted.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Combine beans; divide into four equal batches, about 3 3/4 cups each.
To make one batch of soup:
Wash one batch of beans. Place in a large kettle; add enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil; cook
for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 1 hour.
Tie spices in a cheesecloth bag.
Drain and rinse beans.
Return to kettle; add spices and water.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender, stirring occasionally.
Remove spices.
Add tomatoes and heat through.
Yield:
One batch makes 14 servings (3 1/2 quarts). Diabetic Exchanges:
One serving (1 cup) equals: 2 starch, 1 vegetable, 1/2 meat, also, 191 calories, 293 mg sodium, 0 mg cholesterol, 35 gm carbohydrate, 13 gm protein and 1 gm fat.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in a black pot and brown chicken well.
Remove and brown sausage.
Remove. Add onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, Ro-Tel tomatoes, sage and thyme.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add chicken and sausage and simmer until chicken becomes tender.
Add rice, green onions and parsley.
Stir and add enough water to cover ingredients plus 1 inch.
Bring to a boil and taste for seasoning.
Cover and cook on low heat until rice is tender, about 30 minutes.

title: microwave stuffed bell peppers
directions: Slice tops off peppers and remove seeds.
Stand peppers up in a 9-inch square microwave safe dish.
In a medium bowl, combine onion, cracker crumbs, ketchup, garlic salt, thyme, Italian seasoning and red pepper.
Add ground meat and mix well.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture, dividing evenly.
Pour tomatoes or Ro-Tel with their juices around peppers.
Cover tightly with microwave safe plastic wrap.

title: pizza bread
directions: In a large pan, melt cheese and butter on low heat.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Spread on French bread slices and put under the broiler until cheese is hot and bubbly.
Will keep well in the refrigerator.

title: easy cabbage rolls
directions: Chop or shred cabbage.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Add instant rice to hamburger mixture and mix well.
Spoon mixture on top of shredded cabbage.
Mix soup, water, sugar, catsup and Worcestershire sauce together.
Pour soup mixture over hamburger rice mixture.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until cabbage is tender.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour and salt.
Cut in Crisco to crumble consistency.
Mix together the egg, vinegar and water; add to flour mixture.
Work together to make dough.
If dough is too dry, add more water than recipe calls for to make a nice soft dough, but not too sticky.
Refrigerate dough in wax paper until ready to use, or can use right away.

title: pennies from heaven
directions: Mix ingredients together, except carrots.
Pour over carrots while still hot.
Marinate for 24 hours.
Keeps 2 to 3 weeks.

title: strawberry angel food delight
directions: Hollow out bottom of cake to make a shell, reserving cake pieces.
Whip 1 package of Dream Whip. Add strawberries and cake pieces.
Fill shell with mixture. Frost cake with remaining package of Dream Whip. Use a few nice strawberries for garnish. Chill and serve.

title: heavenly bits
directions: Mix. Roll in balls. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar when cool.

title: fish on the grill
directions: Use heavy aluminum foil.
Cut into large squares.
Place equal portions of the fish fillets on each piece of foil.
In a saucepan melt margarine.
Add lemon juice, parsley, dill, salt and pepper. Stir to blend well.
Pour this mixture over the fish, sprinkle with paprika and top with the onion slices which have been separated into rings.
Fold the foil around the mixture securely. Leave a little space for the food to expand while cooking.
Place on hot grill and grill for 5 to 7 minutes per side until done. Yield: 4 servings.
Carbohydrate 3 g, protein 20 g, fat 7 g, calories 156.

title: sausage roll
directions: Note:
Pork sausage should be room temperature.

title: lasagne bolognese
directions: Melt margarine.
Blend in flour, milk and cream.
Stir over moderate heat until sauce bubbles and is smooth.
Add salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Cook lasagne noodles in boiling salted water.
Strain, rinse and spread on damp towel.
In a large pan or dish, spread thin layers of Meat Sauce Bolognese cream sauce and cheese.
Repeat layers ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes until bubbly hot and top is browned.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cut and serve for 6 to 8 jumbo portions add pound cottage cheese.
If you like, use more Parmesan cheese or use Mozzarella cheese on top. Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate fontants
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll up into little balls.
Put on wax paper. Then melt chocolate in boiler.
Then melt paraffin in double boiler. Mix chocolate and paraffin. Dip balls in chocolate. Place on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: turkey burgers
directions: In bowl, combine turkey, margarine, water and broth mix.
Form into 2 patties.
Spray skillet with Pam and heat over medium-high heat.
Add patties and brown on both sides.
Reduce heat to low and add onions.
Cover pan and cook until patties are no longer pink inside, 5 to 8 minutes.
Serve each burger topped with 2 teaspoons ketchup and half the cooked onion slices on toasted rolls.

title: layered dessert
directions: Cream together flour and oleo; add nuts.
Press into cake pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix together 8 ounces cream cheese, 1 cup powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Fold into cream cheese mixture and spread over cooled crust.
Mix together cold milk and pudding.
Beat until creamy and pour over first layer. Spread rest of Cool Whip over the top and sprinkle with crushed walnuts.

title: cheese ball 'n crackers
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and make a large ball. Put nuts on waxed paper and roll ball in nuts until completely covered.
Refrigerate for at least 1 day ahead.
Serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream butter in blender.
Gradually add sugar; blend well. Combine dry ingredients.
Add with creamed mixture alternately with pumpkin, starting and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan. Cool and remove from pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: bacon mushroom roll-ups
directions: With a rolling pine, flatten each piece of bread leaving the crust on.
Place one large tablespoon of soup and spread onto slice of bread.
Roll up bread, secure with toothpicks.
Cut rolled bread in half.
Wrap 1/2 slice of bacon around filled bread, secure with toothpick.
Bake in 350° oven 15 to 20 minutes until bacon is cooked, turning occasionally.
Enjoy!!

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Bring water to a boil. Add oats to boiling water (turn off heat) and let oats stand for 20 minutes. Cream sugar and butter. Beat eggs into mixture. Sift dry ingredients together. Add to creamed mixture. Add oats and beat well. Bake in greased 8-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Lay down paper on table and put waxed paper on top of paper. Measure oatmeal and peanut butter in a large bowl.
Set aside.

title: creme puff cake
directions: Put water, margarine, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Bring to full, rolling boil.
Add flour all at once and stir vigorously with wooden spoon until mixture forms a thick, smooth ball that leaves the sides of the pan clean.
Remove heat and add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg until paste is shiny and smooth.
Spread paste in jelly roll pan and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Mix altogether.
Freeze.
Use as needed.
Great to have on hand for company.

title: three bean hot dish
directions: Cut up and brown the bacon, then mix in hamburger and onion. Brown all together.
Add all beans. Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients (except coconut and vanilla) in heavy saucepan. Cook until thick, stirring to prevent scorching.
Take off heat; add coconut and vanilla flavoring.
Have pie shell browned ahead of time.
Pour mixture into shell and make meringue.

title: old fashioned (strawberry) shortcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks; beat.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add the sifted ingredients alternately with the milk.
Beat well.
Fold in the well-beaten egg whites.

title: lala's nutty grahams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Melt margarine.
Stir in brown sugar and set aside.
Layer crackers in pan side by side.
Spoon margarine and brown sugar mixture evenly over the crackers, then sprinkle the nuts on top.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes or until bubbly.
Let cool.
Crackers should break evenly on original cracker lines.
Store in a tightly covered container. Yields 48.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350°.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: In small bowl combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Add more water if a thinner sauce is desired.
Refrigerate.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Mix tomatoes, bay leaf, sugar, salt, pepper and onion.
Simmer about 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix butter, flour and milk to make a sauce.
Slowly add the hot tomato mixture to the sauce.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: cherry banana bread
directions: Drain maraschino cherries, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
Cut cherries in quarters; set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, oil, water and nuts together and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: pound cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Whip the whites and add 6 level tablespoons sugar.
Place mixture in refrigerator until the rest is made. Cream butter; add 2 2/3 cups sugar and whip until light (about 10 minutes).
Add flour, coffee cream and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites until well mixed.
Pour into lightly greased Bundt pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
(Cake should fall.)

title: applesauce
directions: Place all ingredients in pan.
Cover and cook over medium heat.
Stir occasionally for about 1/2 hour.

title: hot dip
directions: Chop onion and peppers in blender.
Add tomatoes, cumin, Accent, garlic powder and salt.
Blend all this together.
After everything is chopped and blended, pour in a bowl.
Add table oil. Cook in microwave for 5 minutes.
(You can add as many peppers as you want for hotter taste.)

title: dutch salad
directions: Mix the cabbage, peppers, onion and sugar and let stand while preparing the rest.
Bring to a boil the Wesson oil, vinegar, mustard, celery seed and salt and pour the hot mix over the cabbage.
Refrigerate for 6 hours.
It will stay crisp.
Keep covered.

title: ice cream dessert (1)
directions: Mix margarine with crumbs and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix 1/2 of 1/2-gallon ice cream, pudding and milk.
Beat 4 minutes. Spread on Ritz crackers.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Chill in refrigerator, if using same day, or freeze up to 4 months.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add sugar and water.
Stir to melt margarine and sugar. Add 1 cup chopped apples and stir.
Let stand while preparing pastry.

title: crab melt
directions: Melt butter and cheese over low heat.
Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and mix well.
Process in blender until smooth.
In a bowl, fold in crab meat and pimentos and mix well.
Slice bread in half-inch slices and spread with crab mixture.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 20 slices.

title: chocolate zucchini cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray Bundt, tube or 9 x 13-inch pan with Joy.
Combine cake mix and cinnamon in large mixing bowl. Add eggs, water and oil.
Mix well.
Fold in zucchini and pour into prepared pan.
Bake Bundt or tube for 40 to 50 minutes.
If using a 9 x 13-inch pan, bake for 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely and frost with icing (Cream Cheese Frosting follows). Cake may be served without icing as well.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Place hot dogs in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Slit each one lengthwise.
Put slice of cheese in slit.
Pile mashed potatoes over hot dogs, covering well.
Sprinkle onion over mashed potatoes.
Pour ketchup over onions, using enough so that each hot dog has about 2 teaspoons on it.
Cover with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until cheese is melted and hot dogs are browned.

title: trash
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips in saucepan, stirring to mix well.
Pour over mixture of cereal, raisins, dates and peanuts in bowl.
Mix to coat well.
Add to confectioners sugar in a large trash bag; shake to coat well.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 6 pounds.

title: crab snacks
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Spread on each muffin half.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cut each muffin half into quarters. Broil 3 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine meat, egg, onion, milk, corn flakes, salt and pepper. Form into patties, roll in flour.
Brown in shortening.
Place on cookie sheet; cover with mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place diced chicken in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Mix together 1 can of soup and sour cream.
Spread over chicken.
In a skillet, melt butter or oleo; add the crushed crackers.
Remove from stove; add poppy seed.
Spread over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 6.

title: buttermilk waffles
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients. Separate eggs. Add buttermilk, butter and vanilla. Stir with rubber spatula. Whip whites until fluffy. Incorporate. Pour in dry ingredients. Pour 1/4 cup batter into each section belgium waffle maker. Cook 5 to 7 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix together the jello and boiling water.
Add oranges, pineapple, Cool Whip and sherbet.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend sugar and cinnamon.
Grease 10-inch tube pan.
Dust pan with 1 tablespoon sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Blend cake mix, applesauce and eggs until moistened. Beat as directed on package.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups batter.
Pour remaining batter into pan; sprinkle with rest of sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Top with rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: philadelphia ice cream
directions: Cook all ingredients (except fruit and whipping cream) in double boiler until spoon is murky.
Add to freezer with cream and churn 15 minutes.
Add peaches or bananas and churn until firm.

title: munching peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together the sugar and syrup. Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes, until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup.
Blend well.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 more minutes. (Peanuts are browned and syrup is hot.)
Add baking powder and stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture into greased cookie sheet.
Cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
Break into pieces.

title: marie's pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and butter.
Add eggs and pecans; mix well.
Pour filling in shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar well until smooth.
Spread over the cool crust in pizza pan.

title: party mix (microwave)
directions: Mix Worcestershire sauce, butter, garlic and seasoning salt; melt in microwave (approximately 1 minute).
Pour over other ingredients and mix well.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes and then stir.
Do this 4 times.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and cream until smooth.
Blend in flour.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until cookies begin to turn brown.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and garlic in skillet until browned. Add seasonings and tomato soup.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Add cheese.
Cook slowly, stirring until cheese melts.
Stir in rice and let cool.
Cut peppers in halves lengthwise.
Remove all the inside.
Cook in boiling salted water (cover peppers with water) until barely tender, approximately 3 minutes.
Drain and cool. Place peppers in shallow pan.
Stuff with rice mixture.

title: frozen lemon loaf
directions: Line bottom and sides of an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan with aluminum foil, extending the foil 1 inch over the edges of pan.
Arrange vanilla wafers, top side down, on the bottom of pan, overlapping to fit bottom.
In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped topping, then place the mixture over vanilla wafers.
Cover and freeze 4 hours.
Invert onto a plate and peel off foil.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften and mix with beater or fork.
Blend in sauces and lemon juice.
Add nuts.
Shape in ball.
Roll in nuts and chill.
(Could be rolled in parsley.)

title: banana fritters chinese dessert
directions: Combine 1 cup of the flour, the baking powder, soda and salt in a large bowl.
Gradually blend in water beating with a whisk until smooth.
Peel bananas.
Cut each banana crosswise into three pieces, making a total of 12 pieces.
Coat bananas lightly with remaining 1/2 cup flour.
Heat oil in wok over medium-high heat until it reaches 375°.
Dip banana pieces in flour-water mixture, coating completely.
Cook 4 to 6 pieces at a time in the oil until golden, 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve with ice cream.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: posey's pudding
directions: Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with ice cream, coffee cream or commercial sour cream.

title: baked brisket
directions: Mix all ingredients except barbecue sauce and the teaspoon salt.
Marinate brisket overnight in this.
Cover with foil and bake at 275° for 3 hours.
Remove foil.
Pour barbecue sauce over meat and bake 1 more hour.
Total baking time 4 hours.

title: creole eggs
directions: Cook vegetables together until done.
Add salt and pepper. Make cream sauce out of next 5 ingredients.
Cut eggs in half; put in casserole.
Add alternately vegetables and cream cheese. Sprinkle a little of the cracker crumbs between layers; sprinkle remaining on top.
Heat for 15 to 20 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple, pie filling and nuts in an ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over ingredients.
Slice 2 sticks of margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until crusty and golden.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix in order given like pie crust.
Makes 2 double or 4 single pie shells.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and blend well.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Bake in unbaked pie crust for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: italian beef sandwiches
directions: Put roast in pan with water (half full); cook until well done. After meat is done, slice paper thin.
Put juice with bell peppers and onions in pan; add beef bouillon cube and boil.
Eat with French bread.

title: barbecue pecans
directions: Melt oleo and mix.
Pour over pecans.
Spread on cookie sheets.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Pour half of mixture into a greased pan.
Spread cheese on top.
Pour remaining mixture over top of cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: espresso orange blanc mange
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and cornstarch in a heavy saucepan; mix well.
Add milk, Espresso, Grand Marnier and vanilla and place pot over medium heat.
Bring mixture to a simmer and stir constantly until it thickens (about 3 to 4 minutes).
Spoon into a 4-cup bowl or 4 individual dishes.
Cover and chill well before serving. Garnish with orange.

title: italian stuffed squash
directions: Wash squash; cut in half lengthwise.
Cook, cut side down, in microwave for about 3 minutes.
Carefully scoop out pulp with spoon, leaving about half in shell.
Chop pulp.
Heat oleo in small skillet over medium heat.
Add onion; saute until lightly browned.

title: punch
directions: Mix citric acid, 7 cups of sugar and boiling water and let stand overnight.
When ready, add pineapple juice, orange juice and water.
Mix together and serve.

title: sausage cheese bake
directions: Cook sausage in skillet until browned, stirring to crumble. Drain and set aside.
Unroll each half of crescent roll dough, making a rectangle.
Line bottom and 1/2 inch up sides of a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with rectangles, pressing seams securely to seal.
Sprinkle sausage over dough.
Top with shredded cheese and green pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over casserole.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil water and sugar for 3 minutes and cool.
Mix together remaining ingredients and freeze to slush.
Add 2 or 3 quarts of ginger ale.
Can be frozen and allowed to thaw to slush stage the day of using.
Serves 40.

title: green bean pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Heat beans and 1-inch salted water to boiling.
Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Cover and cook until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain.

title: billy parker's homemade chili
directions: Brown chili meat; drain.
Add chopped onions and all other ingredients, except beans.
Cook about 2 1/2 hours, simmering or a slow boil. Then add beans and simmer another 30 minutes.
Chili hot beans are optional.

title: swedish coffee cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar about 5 minutes on medium speed.
Mix dry ingredients and add; mix for 1 minute.
Add milk and butter; mix at low speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) round or square well-greased and floured pans.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: inside out ravioli
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain macaroni. In skillet cook onion, garlic and ground beef until meat is browned.
Drain fat.

title: edible aquarium
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups ice and water.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
(If mixture is still thin, refrigerate until slightly thickened.)
Pour thickened gelatin into 4 dessert dishes.
Place gummy fish in gelatin.
Refrigerate until set, about 1 hour.
Fun dessert for kids.

title: lasagna hamburger casserole
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Add chopped green onions. Brown hamburger in butter.
Add cut up garlic, salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Cook 5 minutes and cool for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Drain.
Alternate layers of noodles, cream cheese mixture and meat sauce.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all at once in a 2-quart bowl for 30 seconds.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: holiday salad
directions: Arrange all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix dressing and pour over fruit.
Serves 8.

title: sauce piquant
directions: Mix and cook the first five ingredients.
Cook until transparent.
Then add remaining ingredients, except meat.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add shrimp, oysters, chicken, etc., individually or combinations.
Don't thin sauce unless necessary.
Adjust seasonings to taste.
Cook until done, stirring often.
Serve over rice.

title: stuffed spinach and cheese pasta shells
directions: Squeeze spinach dry.
Transfer spinach to large bowl.
Add Ricotta, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, basil and garlic to bowl.
Season with salt and pepper.
Blend together.
Preheat oven to 350°. Spoon 1/2 cup marinara sauce evenly over bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Fill each pasta shell with spinach mixture.
Place shells, filling side up, in dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over shells.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover loosely with foil and bake until heated through, about 30 minutes.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Place beef and vegetables in large casserole in order given. Pour tomato juice or V-8 juice over contents.
Sprinkle salt, sugar and instant tapioca on top.
Paprika may be added, as well as a bay leaf or a pinch of thyme, if desired.

title: italian lemon ice
directions: Soften lemon ice slightly.
Beat in lemon rind and Strega liqueur.
Chill.
Cut lemons in half.
Discard seeds.
With a melon baller, cut scoops or balls from melons and replace them in the melons.
Top with generous portions of lemon ice.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix brown gravy as package states.
Then add onion, bell pepper, tomatoes and soy sauce.
Cook until thick.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over cooked steak.
Serve with rice.

title: cheese bread
directions: Slice French bread in half.
Butter both sides.
Spread Cheez Whiz on buttered bread.
Spread mayonnaise on top of Cheez Whiz and buttered French bread.
Sprinkle Salad Supreme on top.
Broil until lightly toasted.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Mix together cocoa, oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt and add to egg mixture.
Bake in greased 13 X 9
pan.

title: texas pecan candy cake(make at least 2 weeks ahead so flavors can mellow.)
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Grease and flour 9
x 13-inch tube pan with removable bottom.
Set aside.
Combine cherries, pineapple and dates in a very large bowl.
Sprinkle with flour.
Toss to coat well; add pecans and coconut and toss to mix.
Add sweetened condensed milk; stir to mix well.
Spoon evenly into prepared pan, smoothing top.
Bake in preheated 250° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan on rack.
Remove from pan.
Wrap tightly in foil. Refrigerate at least 2 weeks.
Cake cuts best when cold.
Slice very thin with serrated knife.

title: rousso's sauteed crabmeat
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter until tender, but not mushy.
Add crabmeat and sherry; cook until heated through. Garnish with lemon and parsley.
Makes 4 small or 2 large servings.

title: mock chicken roast
directions: Pour water over bread crumbs and let stand while mixing other ingredients.
Saute onion and celery in corn oil.
Mix all ingredients.
Put into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Center must be firm.
This roast is good baked one day and reheated the next.

title: tailgate party salad
directions: Prepare rotini according to package directions. Drain. Combine all ingredients. Toss well to mix. Cover and chill thoroughly.
Toss gently before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: italian vinaigrette
directions: Combine ingredients in a large jar with a tight fitting lid. Shake well.
Makes 2 cups.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients; stir in the okra.
Pour oil to depth of 2 inches in Dutch oven.
Heat to 350°.
Drop mixture by spoonful into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown, turning once. Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with salt, if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In large bowl, beat milk and peanut butter until smooth. Add Bisquick and vanilla; mix well.
Shape into 1 inch balls. Roll in sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with fork. Bake 6 to 8 minutes. Cool.

title: cranberry apple casserole
directions: Combine apples, cranberries and 2 tablespoons flour; toss to coat fruit.
Add sugar, mixing well.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Combine oatmeal, chopped pecans, 1/2 cup flour and brown sugar.
Add margarine; stir well.
Spoon over fruit mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Serve with tortilla chips and grated cheese. Makes a large pot of soup.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for 2 hours before rolling out dough.
Roll out 3/8-inch thick.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: carob brownies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs alternately with flour, carob powder and salt, sifted together.
Add vanilla and nuts. Put in greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: doughnuts (lottie thomas)
directions: Mix together
yeast
with
water
water.
Melt
shortening. Add sugar and salt.
Beat eggs and add to yeast mixture with seasonings and shortening.
Add flour.
Let rise.
Roll out on bit of floured surface. Fry and glaze
or
roll
in powdered sugar or cinnamon mixture.
Yield: 75.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Mix flour, butter and sugar together.
Pat onto a cookie sheet (one with an edge all the way around).
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Let it cool.
Mix the Dream Whip, milk and vanilla. Beat until stiff.
Add cream cheese and mix until blended completely. Spread onto cooled crust.
Top with the pie filling.
Be sure to refrigerate.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Soften butter and mix all ingredients together in large bowl. Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper until set.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook meat until tender and falls from bone.
Add all ingredients together and cook slowly for one hour.
According to desired consistency of stew, you may add additional broth.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat on medium speed 2 full minutes.
Pour in 3 x 8-inch cake pans which have been greased and dusted with flour.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Pineapple Frosting (see icings).

title: fettucine with mushrooms and salami
directions: Cook mushrooms in butter over moderate heat for 10 minutes, or until liquid has evaporated and butter is golden.
Stir in salami, scallions and pepper; cook for 3 minutes.
Beat cream with egg yolks and Parmesan cheese.
Cook fettucine "al dente."
Drain. Toss with cream mixture.
Transfer to serving dish; spoon mushroom sauce over pasta.

title: chop suey
directions: Freeze steak partially in
order
to
cut
it into very thin 3-inch strips.
Brown in oil in skillet.
Add vegetables, water, soup mix and soy
sauce.
Cover;
simmer over low heat. Stir occasionally for 20 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and water; stir into meat mixture
until
sauce is thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: sugar cookies like grandma's(lower cholesterol)
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients, then add oil and beat well.
Beat in eggs well.
Add dry ingredients.
Refrigerate dough at least 3 hours or overnight for easier handling.
Make cookies by rolling dough into small balls (walnut size) and flatten with glass dipped in sugar/flour mixture (2 tablespoons each) on oiled cookie sheets at 375° for 10 minutes.
I use pressed glass to get design in cookie.
Fun for grandchildren.

title: hidden valley potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; do not peel.
Slice crossways; layer in a casserole dish.
Pour melted butter over potatoes and sprinkle with Hidden Valley mix.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: superb sauce for steak
directions: Saute shallot in butter until golden.
Blend in flour, stock, red wine, vinegar and salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes, then add heavy cream.
Mix lightly.
Broil a thick, juicy steak and pour sauce over it.

title: bourbon dogs
directions: Mix all together and bake at 300° for 1 hour, stirring frequently.

title: cowboy potatoes
directions: Steam peeled potatoes with small amount of cooking oil.
When steamed well, drain potatoes and add cooked bacon and onions. Stir in cream of mushroom soup and shredded cheese.
Bake until hot.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Blend together all ingredients and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Will thicken some after it is removed from heat .

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Combine lime and 2 gallons water in large container.
Soak tomatoes in lime water for 24 hours.
Wash carefully and soak in clear water for 5 hours.
Combine vinegar, sugar, celery seed, allspice, cinnamon and salt in large kettle; bring to boiling point.
Pour over tomatoes while hot.
Let stand for 24 hours. Bring to a boil.
Boil for 25 minutes.
Place in sterilized jars and seal.

title: chinese noodles casserole
directions: Brown meat and saute onions. Combine all ingredients, except noodles. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Top with one can Chinese Noodles and bake 15 minutes more.

title: nobby apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and mix well. Add apples, nuts and vanilla.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: curry rice salad
directions: Chill for 2
hours.
Then add the last four ingredients.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine mayonnaise, cheese, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Beat egg white with rotary beater until stiff, but not dry.
Fold mayonnaise mixture into beaten egg white. Spoon lightly onto crackers and bake 10 to 15 minutes, until puffy and golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until about done; drain.
Saute celery, green pepper and onion in 1 stick butter until soft and clear.
Add water chestnuts, mushrooms, milk and cheese, stirring well until melted (low heat or cheese will stick).
Mix with macaroni.
Saute bread in 1/2 stick butter and add on top.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours.
Start at 400°.
Turn down to 350°.
Makes a big 2 quarts.

title: overnight date cookies(my grandmother's recipe)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Fold in flour, baking powder and soda.
If too stiff, add 1 tablespoon milk.
Chill dough overnight.
Remove from refrigerator and let stand 15 to 30 minutes. Roll thin on pastry cloth dusted with 10x sugar.
Use about 2-inch round cookie cutter.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° about 8 minutes. Cool and fill.

title: chocolate cheesecake pie(makes one 9-inch pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, sugar, cocoa and margarine.
Press firmly on bottom and up sides of rim of 9-inch pie plate.
In mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then melted chocolate chips. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into prepared crust.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until center is set.
Cool thoroughly. Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and Crisco.
Add egg yolks.
Beat egg whites to fold in later.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk and soda, mixed together.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine all ingredients with small amount of salt and pepper. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop a small teaspoon of dough on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: tirami-su
directions: Pour the Mascarpone in a big bowl and stir until it becomes a smooth cream.
Add the 5 yolks and sugar and stir well.
In a separate bowl whip the cream until it becomes very stiff and add the cheese mixture.
Also whip the egg whites until they are stiff and add to the cheese mixture.
Slowly stir all the ingredients to a thick smooth cream.
Add the liqueur to the coffee.
In an oblong Pyrex container cover the bottom with a layer of the cream mix, then a layer of biscuits, then pour over them some coffee until each biscuit is soggy.
Repeat this procedure of layering.
The last layer should be cream and sprinkle this with sifted cocoa (not sweet) and refrigerate.
Best made the day before.

title: chicken with wild rice
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Prepare rice per directions on package. Melt butter in 3-quart casserole dish on moderate heat. Add onion; cook 3 minutes, until tender. Sprinkle in flour and stir. Gradually add broth, stirring and heat to boiling point. Gently stir in rice. Rub hens or breasts with butter, salt and pepper. Arrange on rice mixture; cover and bake 45 minutes or until rice and chicken are done.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Cook the ginger root in 2 tablespoons oil over high heat until brown.
Add the chicken; cook with lid on for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Pour into container; set aside.
Put 2 tablespoons oil in pan over high heat.
Add the onion, squash, bean sprouts and bell pepper strips.
Stir frequently until tender.
Add the pineapple and water chestnuts.
Continue stirring until well heated, then pour
in mixture of the pineapple juice, cornstarch and soy sauce.
Stir until thickens.
Serve over cooked brown rice.
May vary vegetables to your own taste.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops from peppers and remove seed.
Soak in solution of 1 cup salt in 4 quarts water (cold).
Let stand 24 hours in cool place.
Drain; rinse.
Drain well.
Cut cabbage as for cole slaw. For each quart of cabbage, add 1 teaspoon salt and pepper and mustard seed (I use only salt).
Pack into peppers.
Combine white vinegar, 2 cups water and sugar.
Bring to boil.
Pack peppers into hot jars.
Cover with boiling vinegar and seal.
(Can use long yellow or round hot peppers.
I prefer the long yellow.)
I often put a sweet stuffed pepper in the jar with the hot ones.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Combine eggs, milk and butter; blend well.
Fold in dry ingredients; add corn last. Drop by tablespoon into hot vegetable oil and deep fry for about 5 minutes, or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serve warm.

title: orange dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O and cottage cheese together.
Add oranges and Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 4 ingredients; cook over medium heat.
Drain.
Add tomatoes and next 3 ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Combine 1 cup American cheese with cottage cheese and egg.
Heat oil in pan. Cut tortillas into quarters and cook in oil.

title: graham cracker fluff
directions: Beat egg yolks and add sugar and milk.
Cook in top of double boiler until slightly thickened.
Soak gelatin in cold water. Pour hot mixture over softened gelatin and stir until smooth. Chill until slightly thickened.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla to chilled mixture.
Beat whipping cream until stiff and add to mixture.
Combine melted butter, sugar and graham crumbs. Sprinkle most of the crumbs in 11 x 7-inch dish.
Pour mixture over crumbs and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Let chill in fridge until set.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tortilla-bean casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cut up tomatoes with juice.
Add picante sauce, onion, green pepper, garlic and cumin.
Bring to a boil; then reduce heat and simmer fro 10 minutes.
Add kidney beans (may substitute 1 can of Great Northerns for 1 can of kidney beans).

title: oreo crunch
directions: Crush cookies and spread in bottom of a large dish.
Spread ice cream over cookies.
Pour syrup over ice cream.
Spread Cool Whip over syrup and freeze.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Blend well butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add dry vanilla pudding.
Mix well.
Add milk and blend well.
Add Cool Whip and blend well.
Put cookies in blender and blend until mixture looks like dirt.
Next, layer in serving dish, cookies first and then pudding.
Alternate layers, ending with cookies.
Keep refrigerated.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a piece of bacon.
Cover bottom of flat, greased baking dish (about 8 x 12 x 2-inch) with chipped beef.
Arrange chicken breasts on chipped beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over all.
Refrigerate.
When ready to bake, bake at 375° for 3 hours, uncovered.
Serves 8.

title: papa's chicken
directions: Coat chicken with mayonnaise.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: duncan hines cherry fudge cake
directions: Mix by hand and pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: creamy chicken and mushrooms
directions: Add 1 teaspoon hot margarine in skillet.
Cook chicken until browned on both sides.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand for 20 minutes. Cream sugars, eggs and oleo.
Add flour, salt, soda and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: candy cookies
directions: Bring the sugar and syrup to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Mix with remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop on wax paper to harden.
Makes about 5 or 6 dozen.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender; drain. Add beef, cheese, soup, milk, onion and peas.
Pour into greased 3-quart casserole.
Top with bread dressing crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until peas are tender and cheese is melted.

title: chicken with banana and coconut
directions: Makes 2 servings.
Heat frying pan and add olive oil, then cook chicken until almost firm.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook until hot (3 to 4 minutes) and serve.

title: great gram holbrook's chocolate pudding
directions: Scald milk in a double boiler.
Sift sugar, cornstarch and cocoa together.
With a little warm water, dissolve the sugar mixture into a syrup.
Add to milk and cook until thick, remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.

title: pig cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When cake is done and cool, prepare topping.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken pieces between plastic.
Flatten with a rolling pin.
Dip chicken in beaten eggs and dredge in flour, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper mixture.

title: cheese puff appi-teasers
directions: Mix above.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes on lightly greased cookie sheet.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with aluminum foil.
Season chicken as desired.
Mix cream of chicken soup, cream of celery soup, rice and water.
Place in pan.
Arrange chicken pieces on top of mixture.

title: susan's no-knead rolls
directions: Mix together thoroughly and add 5 to 7 cups flour, enough so dough pulls away from bowl. Cover with damp cloth and let rise for 30 minutes in a warm place.
Spoon into greased muffin pans and let rise another 30 minutes. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes (until golden brown).

title: stuffed seashells
directions: Add cubed bread, egg, oregano, parsley, salt and pepper to hamburger.
Parboil seashells.
Cover baking dish bottom with Ragu with mushrooms or meat.
Fill shells with hamburger mix.
Place side by side.
Cover with sauce.
After baked, sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Let melt.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peach tree ribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving-size pieces and place in a large pot. Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until tender (40 to 50 minutes).
Drain.
Place meat in a shallow baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat. Let marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Drain well, reserving marinade.
Grill ribs over hot coals for 40 to 50 minutes, depending upon thickness.
Baste with marinade frequently during cooking.
Yields 4 servings.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour in a square pan and bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix together and bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: uncle joe's enchiladas
directions: Season
meat with salt and pepper.
Cook with onion and garlic until
almost done.
Mix remaining dry ingredients and stir
into meat.
Add
water,
cook about 15 minutes.
Soften each
tortilla in
hot
oil.
Put
chopped
onion and grated Longhorn
cheese on soft tortilla and roll up.
Place in pan. Top with chili mix. Sprinkle with onion and cheese.
Place in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Let the lightly salted zucchini stand 15 minutes.
Squeeze out the excess moisture.
Combine zucchini with 2 beaten eggs, flour, Parmesan, 1/2 cup Mozzarella and a little salt and pepper to taste. Spread this mixture into a greased baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until the surface is firm and dry.
Spread a very small amount of olive oil over the surface and broil 5 minutes.

title: tom vertin's imitation trail mix
directions: The average number of M&M's per package is 57.
Of these, 33% are dark brown, 25% are yellow, 19% orange, 14% light brown and 9% green.
(Done in 1984, before red was re-added).
Each M&M has about 4.2 calories.

title: baked fish in microwave
directions: Lay fish fillets evenly into microwavable dish.
Add Sprite, butter, salt and pepper.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook for 12 minutes or longer until fish is flaky.

title: fudge
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients gently for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add last 2 ingredients and pour into 10 1/2 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch buttered, Teflon or wax paper-lined pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Dice chicken into cubes.
Place chicken into casserole dish.
Add soup, sour cream and a little of the broth from the chicken.
Mix and top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Line bottom of baking dish with chicken cubes.
Melt butter and mix with crushed Ritz crackers and poppy seed.
Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with crumb mixture.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut potatoes into large chunks.
In large bowl, add ingredients.
Mix well until potatoes are evenly coated.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or roasting pan, stirring occasionally.
Cook about 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish, if desired, with chopped fresh parsley.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: salmon steaks
directions: Place salmon on microwave-safe plate.
Place a paper towel over top of steaks and microwave on High for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes. Set aside.

title: hunter's chicken
directions: Cut up chicken.
Dredge with flour.
Saute until golden in oil, onion and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Serve over pasta.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Serves 4.

title: seafare-florentine bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange fish in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with salt, onion powder and pepper.
Add 1/3 cup milk or water to can of cheese soup and stir. (Will spread easier.)
Spoon over fish. Top with spinach. Beat remaining ingredients about 1 minute or until almost smooth.
Pour over spinach. Bake, uncovered, about 40 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Remove from oven and let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet over low heat. Lay 3 to 4 lasagna noodles on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish; pour drained hamburger and onion over noodles. Spread sour cream over hamburger; cover with Ragu, then a layer of Swiss cheese and Mozzarella cheese, using half of each. Begin another layer of noodles, meat, sauce and cheeses, adding Parmesan cheese. The second layer has no sour cream. Be sure to cover all noodles with sauce and cheese. Add additional sauce to cover top completely. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until noodles are tender. Let set before serving.

title: krispie krunchies
directions: Cream margarine.
Blend in sugar and mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Put in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
(A larger pan may be used for thinner bars.)
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Spread marshmallows on top of hot mixture.
Return to oven for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Melt and blend chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies.
Spread on top.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, egg, sugar and salt.
Add 3 cups of the flour.
Beat well.
Add remaining flour and stir into a smooth ball.
Place into a greased bowl, turning over to grease top.
Cover and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and turn over.
Cover with a damp cloth.
Place into refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Shape as needed and let rise 1 1/2 hours until light.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop on cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in an airtight container.
To use:
Add boiling water and mix to taste.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and save juice;
slice bananas.
Pour lemon juice over
bananas.
Do
not
use
juice
of cherries.
Cook pudding according to package instructions using 1 3/4 cups of drained fruit
juice
instead
of
milk.
Cool, then mix with fruit. Put in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.

title: southern pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients except baking soda in a 4-quart casserole, stirring well.
Microwave at High for 12 to 13 minutes, stirring every 4 minutes.
Stir in baking soda.
Microwave at High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Beat with wooden spoon until mixture begins to thicken.
Working rapidly, drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased wax paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass). Grease and flour loaf pan.
Beat shortening, sugar and lemon rind or extract until creamy. Beat in egg. Add dry ingredients. Stir in mashed ripe bananas until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass pan) for 1 hour.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix confectioners sugar, butter and whiskey until like dough. Cover; put in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours.
Form into small balls, putting pecan in each center.
Melt in double boiler chocolate, butter and paraffin.
Dip each ball in melted chocolate mixture. Put small pecan on top.
Place on waxed paper.

title: zucchini beef casserole
directions: Saute zucchini and mushrooms in vegetable oil until tender. Drain well and set aside.
Cook and ground beef and onion in skillet until meat is browned.
Drain off drippings.
Stir in tomato sauce, flour, oregano, basil, salt and pepper. Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: raisin sour cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, nutmeg and salt in a 2-quart saucepan. Stir in sour cream.
Stir in raisins, lemon juice and egg yolks. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with Brown Sugar Meringue (in Beverages, Microwave & Miscellaneous Section).

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix dry
ingredients
together.
Then
in
the top of a double boiler,
slowly
add milk to the dry ingredients, stirring constantly.
Cook over boiling water until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.

title: "lo-fat" chicken fajitas
directions: Prepare grill by placing heavy-duty aluminum foil over grill and spraying with Pam (or nonstick spray). Note:
Do not spray foil while grill is on.
Light grill after spraying.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells as directed on box but add 1 tablespoon of oil to prevent from sticking together.

title: shrimp, scallop or chicken bisello
directions: Oil a 10-inch saute pan.
Dust and flour shrimp, scallops or chicken and lightly saute.
Add garlic, basil, salt and pepper; stir in white wine.
Put in tomatoes, pat of butter and flour. Stir and simmer 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve over your favorite pasta.

title: cooked potato salad dressing
directions: Cook, stirring until thick.
This makes enough for 1/2 to 1 gallon potatoes.
May add pickles, onion and garlic salt.

title: lemon snowball(dazzle your guests with this snow-capped lemon cloud.)
directions: Line a 12-cup bowl with 2 pieces of wax paper one on top of the other.
Let each piece extend over opposite edges of bowl so all edges are covered; paper will be wrinkled.
Set bowl aside.

title: broccoli and tomato fettuccine
directions: Cook and stir broccoli in dressing 2 minutes.
Cook tomatoes in small saucepan over low heat 5 minutes.
Serve over fettuccine. Top with Kraft 100% grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg.
Mix in apples and nuts. Add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: diet orange pudding
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water to soften.
Add boiling water and put into blender which already contains sweetener, extract and ice cubes.
Blend until ice is homogenized.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour onto buttered griddle.

title: broccoli-stuffed tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes thoroughly.
Cut tops from tomatoes; scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Reserve pulp for other uses. Sprinkle cavity of each tomato with salt and pepper and invert on wire rack to drain 30 minutes.
Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting salt.
Drain well.
Combine broccoli and next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Stuff tomato shells with broccoli mixture; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: snickers bars
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening over hot water.
Stir until smooth.
Pour 1/2 into 8-inch foil-lined pan, spreading evenly. Refrigerate until firm (about 15 minutes).
Return remaining chocolate to low heat.

title: old fashioned sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix well.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Heat oven to 400° and let brown slightly.
Turn off heat and let stay in oven for 15 minutes.
Do not cook until dry.

title: quick beef soup
directions: Mix together in large soup pot and cook.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix until consistency of corn meal.
Slightly beat 2 egg yolks and almost finish filling a 1 cup measure with ice water.
Add 2 teaspoons vinegar, if desired.
This dough handles well and freezes well.
Makes 5 pie crusts.

title: twice and more rice krispies treats
directions: Melt butter in largest nonstick saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Using wax paper, press mixture into buttered pan (or pans).
Cut into squares when cool.
Enjoy!!

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix brown sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs and mix well. Add flour (can
sift
if
you
want to) and mix.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Line 9 x 13-inch glass dish with foil.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pie crust(no roll)
directions: Mix dry ingredients in 9-inch pie plate. Combine oil and milk and mix with fork.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Stir until all is moistened.
Press out with fingers and up sides of plate.
Flute edge. Bake according to directions on recipe for 1 crust pie.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and onion.
Place in boiler with enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil and continue boiling until squash are tender.
Layer squash, cheese and Waverly crackers. Continue until you have used all of your squash.
(Usually 2 to 3 layers.)
Top with margarine and pour enough milk around the edge until it reaches the top.
Place in a 350° oven for approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: creamy orange smoothie
directions: Process all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Pour into serving glasses and serve.
Makes 6 servings.
Or, can mix and freeze.
Transfer to refrigerator 30 to 40 minutes before to slightly soften.

title: fried chicken tacos
directions: Add salt to chicken.
Mix well.
Place 1 tortilla on a dry comal or frying pan to heat it and make it pliable.
Heat on both sides.
Remove to a plate.
Continue with remaining tortillas. Put a strip of chicken down the center of each tortilla and roll. Either secure with a toothpick or lay them side by side in a baking pan.
Heat oil in a large, heavy frying pan until smoking. With tongs, place each tortilla in hot oil.
Fry until crispy, about 6 minutes, and drain well.
Remove toothpicks.
Top with guacamole and salsa.
Serve immediately.
Makes 12 tacos.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 9-inch, deep baking dish.
Mix soups and milk; heat until very warm and smooth.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle stuffing crumbs over mixture.
Mix margarine and broth; pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients into a bowl.
Blend on medium speed until smooth and well mixed.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 - 55 minutes.

title: chicken with peanuts
directions: Debone chicken.
Use bones to make broth or use bouillon cube. Heat 2 tablespoons oil in wok and saute chicken 5 minutes. Remove chicken.
Add remaining oil with garlic on toothpicks (to remove easily).
Cook until garlic browns.
Rub over wok.
Discard garlic.
Add peanuts, onion, hot sauce, chicken, soy sauce and sugar.
Cook a few minutes.
Stir in broth and when it boils, add cornstarch paste and sherry (not cooking sherry).
Cover and simmer until thickens.
Serve over rice.
You can make ahead but do not add peanuts, cornstarch, sugar or sherry until before serving.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1/4 cup butter until tender.
Combine onion, soup, mushrooms, cheese, parsley, salt, pepper, almonds and broccoli.
Mix well.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole.
Combine stuffing mix and 1/4 cup butter.
Spoon over broccoli mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fried okra
directions: Pour milk over okra and let stand 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Toss okra with hands to make sure each piece is soaked.
Mix meal and flour with salt and pepper to taste.
Drain okra and roll in flour mixture.
Drop in hot oil and fry until golden brown.
Repeat until all okra is fried.

title: raisin pumpkin squares
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and nutmeg together.
Beat eggs in separate bowl.
Add sugars gradually; beat well.
Add butter, nuts and raisins.
Add sifted ingredients alternately with pumpkin to egg mixture.
Pour into a greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut into squares.
Makes 16 squares.

title: cherry candy
directions: Melt the chocolate bits over double boiler.
Drain the cherries; pat dry with paper towel.
Dip into chocolate.
Dip into crushed cashew bits.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine sugar and peanut butter into crumbs.
Save a few crumbs for the top.
