Put rest into bottom of 9-inch pie crust. Pour 1 package French vanilla instant pudding (made according to package directions) over crumbs.
Top with Cool Whip and rest of crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix sugar with milk and stir well. Cook on medium heat until it begins to boil.
Continue to boil until mixture reaches the "soft ball" stage* (about 7 minutes). Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and Fluff; beat mixture until all are blended.
Pour into buttered pan; cool, then cut into squares when completely cooled.
Easy and delicious!

title: roast eye of round
directions: Make slashes in roast and tuck into each a sliver of garlic and ginger.
Combine oil, soy sauce and wine.
Put roast and sauce into a sealable plastic bag overnight.
Remove roast from bag and place in a greased shallow roasting pan.
Place in a preheated 450° oven for 30 minutes, 45 minutes for larger roast.
Turn off heat, leaving roast in oven for an additional 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.

title: fudge(low fat)
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and milk over medium heat to boil.
Stir constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir until melted.
Add marshmallow cream and blend.
Put in greased 9 inch pan.
Cut into squares (70 calories).

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple chunks in medium size buttered casserole dish. Mix cornstarch and sugar. Add to pineapple. Stir lightly, but do not stir after this. Sprinkle cheese over pineapple. Sprinkle crackers over cheese.
Pour butter over crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Very good with ham or pork.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer in crock-pot for 4 hours.

title: broccoli cheese dip
directions: Place Cheez Whiz and soups in crock-pot to warm.
Thaw frozen broccoli and drain well (may be cooked, if desired).
Brown hamburger meat, using no seasoning.
Add broccoli and hamburger meat to cheese mixture.
Serve warm.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Thaw pie crusts.
Mix filling with spatula. Prick one of the pie crusts with fork several times and cook for 5 minutes. Add filling to the cooked pie crust. Top with second pie crust.
Crimp edges.
Pierce top for vent. Cook for about 40 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together lightly.
Chill thoroughly.
Just before serving, drain and toss together with mayonnaise to moisten. Serve on crisp lettuce.
Garnish with tomato sections, lemon wedges and sliced hard-cooked eggs.
Serves 4.

title: green bean and italian sausage
directions: *Take link sausage out of jacket.
Use hot or sweet sausage or mix.

title: chocolate chip rocky road pie
directions: Melt butter at low heat.
Mix sugar until well blended.
Add eggs, hot water and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda, add to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Mix nuts and 1/2 cup chips and 1/2 cup marshmallows.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Serve pie with scoop of ice cream.

title: german skillet beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; reserve 2 tablespoons drippings in pan. Crumble bacon; set aside.
Saute onion in drippings until tender. Add bacon and remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until thickened and heated through, stirring occasionally.

title: baked salmon
directions: Wipe the 6 pieces of salmon dry and arrange in a well buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle the grated onion and other seasonings over the top of the fish.
Pour all the cream over the fish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve sprinkled with chopped parsley and lemon wedges.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Cut up chicken and boil until tender.
Take chicken off bones. Put 1/2 of chicken in large casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Put 1/2 cup onions, 1/2 cup celery and 1/2 bag crumbs over chicken.
Mix 2 cups chicken broth with soup.
Pour over mixture in dish.
Place remainder of chicken, celery and crumbs in dish.
Top with other 1 1/2 cups broth.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Roll
each
piece
of
chicken in melted butter or oleo until well coated.
Combine chopped garlic, cheese and crumbs; press firmly
around each piece of chicken.
Bake 45 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.

title: easy tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add other ingredients; mix well. Roll into balls.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork or glass coated with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate.
Sprinkle pecans in pan. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (can use blender).
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: date rolls
directions: Cream sugar and oleo. Add dates. Bring to a boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Add cereal, nuts and vanilla. Take out by teaspoon and roll in coconut.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until it tests done.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese and the powdered sugar together.
Then add Cool Whip and strawberries.
Next, add to graham cracker pie crust.
Let set for at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: banana pudding
directions: Begin mixing condensed milk and water, adding instant pudding simultaneously.
Beat thoroughly with electric mixer.
Put in refrigerator for 10 minutes; begin beating whipping cream.
Take first ingredients and mix thoroughly with whipping cream.
Layer vanilla wafers and sliced bananas.
Pour layer of mixture, then repeat twice.
Cover and refrigerate; enjoy.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Heat
milk
to scalding;
dissolve sugar and shortening in milk in large covered bowl.
Let cool until lukewarm.
Put yeast in small amount of warm water, enough to dissolve yeast. When milk cools to lukewarm, add yeast.
Stir in enough flour until it's
like
cake
batter.
Cover
and let set for 1 1/2 hours. Then
add
salt, soda and baking powder.
Stir in more flour,
it won't be of kneading consistency.
Leave in refrigerator
at least
2 hours.
Can be left overnight.
Take out; roll out rolls, let rise 2 hours before baking.

title: betty's chicken casserole
directions: Mix
in
order	given.	Refrigerate overnight.	Bake at 350° for 1 hour in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Pour scalded milk over bread crumbs.
Stir in butter, onion, cheese and salt.
Mix well.
Beat egg yolks and add.
Stir in cooked macaroni.
Beat egg whites to form soft peaks.
Fold into macaroni mixture.
Pour into buttered casserole and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix yeast with milk and sugar.
Combine flour, soda and salt. Cut shortening into dry mixture with pastry cutter.
Add milk-yeast mixture and stir until ingredients are moist.
Turn out on lightly floured surface.
Knead 4 or 5 times, roll to about 1/2-inch thickness, and cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Dip in melted margarine and place on greased baking sheet.
Let rise, covered, about an hour.
Bake in preheated hot oven 12 minutes or until nicely browned.
Makes about 36.

title: christmas oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, add sugars and cream well.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and milk.
Add flour sifted with soda, baking powder and salt.
Add raisins, coconut and pecans; mix.
Then add oatmeal last.
Mixture will be thick.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheets, flatten slightly and bake about 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: oven-fried pork chops(microwave)
directions: Coat chops as package directs.
Line oblong dish with paper towel. Arrange chops, ribs toward center.
Heat on Medium 15 to 17 minutes.

title: turkey sausage succotash
directions: Heat the oil in 12-inch skillet over moderately high heat for 1 minute. Add the sausage and saut, stirring occasionally for 5 minutes. Drain on paper toweling. Reduce the heat to moderate; add the onion in the skillet. Saut, stirring occasionally, for 3 minutes or until softened. Add the garlic and saut, stirring occasionally, for 2 minutes. Stir in the tomatoes, lima beans, marjoram and pepper. Bring to a boil, then cover and cook for 10 minutes. Stir in the corn and sausage, then return the mixture to a boil. Cover and cook for 5 minutes or until the lima beans are tender and sausage is cooked through. Serves 4.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing well, until blended.
Add lemon juice, pimento, green pepper, onions, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Mix well.
Shape into ball.
Roll in finely chopped dried beef and chill.

title: maple flavored bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Blend in syrup, milk and salt.
Add cereal and bread cubes.
Pour into well-greased 1-quart casserole. Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm. Yields 6 servings.

title: cole slaw dressing(from a&w restaurant)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate until used.
Keeps for several days.

title: cinnamon honey butter
directions: Mix together.
Keep in refrigerator.
Great on toast, French toast, pancakes or waffles.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salad dressing together.
Dissolve cocoa and soda in the water.
Mix liquid with the other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: venison bologna(makes 3 rolls)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Separate into 3 rolls, and cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for 3 days.
Remove from fridge, and bake on oven rack, at 350° for 1 hour.
(Make sure you have drip pan beneath the oven rack.)

title: water chestnut appetizers
directions: Cook bacon about half cooked; wrap around the whole water chestnut.
Place in cake pan and mix tomato catsup and brown sugar together.
Pour over water chestnuts.
Bake until bacon is completely cooked, about 30 minutes, in 350° oven.

title: fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips and milk in pan over medium heat.
When melted, remove from heat. Add salt, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch dish and chill for 2 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop up and mix together cauliflower, broccoli, grated cheese, peas, bacon bits and sunflower seeds.
In separate bowl, mix Miracle Whip, sour cream, garlic powder and sugar.
Stir all together.
Store in refrigerator covered.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix and freeze. Makes 2 quarts vanilla ice cream.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine cranberry and pineapple juices, sugar and almond extract, stirring until sugar dissolves; refrigerate 4 hours. Just before serving, stir in ginger ale.
Yield: 1 gallon.

title: turtle cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended.
Melt caramels with milk on low heat, stirring frequently until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Pour caramel mixture into crust.
Top with cream cheese batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Serves 8.

title: fried squash
directions: Wash and slice squash, soak in salted water 10 to 15 minutes. Dip into cornmeal; fry in shortening until golden brown on both sides.

title: hot mustard dressing
directions: Mix mustard and sugar; add vinegar.
Stir in eggs and cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
If too thick, thin down with extra vinegar, adding a little at a time until desired consistency is reached.

title: cheese and spinach fettuccine
directions: In saucepot, prepare fettuccine as label directs, adding frozen spinach to pot during last 5 minutes of cooking; drain. Return fettuccine to pot; keep warm. In 2-quart pan, mix milk and cornstarch until smooth. Add margarine, salt and nutmeg. Cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens. Cook 1 minute. Stir in grated Parmesan cheese and crumbled Blue cheese. Add sauce to pasta in saucepot. Toss gently until well coated. Makes 4 servings.

title: poppy seed fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges, peaches and pineapple.
Combine all fruit in a large bowl and gently toss.
Combine pudding mix, orange juice and poppy seed in another bowl; mix well.
Pour over fruit and gently toss.
Chill overnight.
Serves 10.

title: shrimp and asparagus casserole
directions: On stove top or in microwave oven, blanch asparagus for 3 minutes.
Drain well; set aside.
In a small saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in the flour; cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Gradually whisk in milk and cream.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in wine (or substitute).
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in beaten egg yolk, cheese and shrimp.
In a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole, arrange half the asparagus.
Pour on half the sauce.
Repeat layers.
Top with buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: southern chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.

title: potage creme a la duberry(cream of cauliflower soup)
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling, salted water for 10 minutes; drain.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add onion and saute until golden.
Add cauliflower and 2 tablespoons of water.
Cover and simmer slowly for 10 minutes.
Add 1 extra tablespoon of water if necessary.
In a large saucepan, bring stock to simmer.
Add cauliflower and simmer 30 minutes, partially covered.
Puree soup, 2 cups at
a time, in blender or food processor.
Just before serving, bring soup to a boil.
Beat yolks with cream and stir into soup off heat.
Garnish with dash of nutmeg, parsley or chervil and croutons.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: holiday cheese tree
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese and cream cheese until blended.
Add 1 tablespoon pimento, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Chill.
Drop 6 (1/3 cup) measures of mixture into triangle shape on a serving platter.
Drop remaining mixture at base of triangle.
Smooth to form tree.
Top with parsley, nuts and remaining pimento.
Serve with Triscuit wafers. Makes 2 cups.

title: scalloped strawberries
directions: Wash and hull strawberries and mix with sugar.
Put alternate layers and bread cubes into a buttered baking dish.
Dot with butter and bake in a hot oven.
Serve hot with cream.
Bake at 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate oil cake
directions: Mix together and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.
This recipe has no eggs and stays real moist.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring water, vinegar and canning salt to a boil.
Wash cucumbers.
Drop in enough cucumbers to fill a quart.
Stir these around when they change color.
Put into jar.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together well.
Add butter and beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each. Add vanilla and buttermilk alternately with flour, soda and salt, which have been sifted together.
Mix well.
Add coconut and pecans.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased and floured layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: creamy hot beef dip
directions: Combine ingredients in a 1-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together. Store in airtight container. Dilute 1 tablespoon to cup.

title: hamburger with rice
directions: Brown meat and drain; add water, rice, onion and soy sauce. Simmer for 25 minutes or until rice is done.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil all the ingredients until hard ball stage (270°).
Add 1/2 teaspoon soda.
Pour over 3 to 4 quarts popped corn.
Stir until every kernel is coated.
When cold, it will not be sticky.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix together with fork, yellow cake mix (minus 1 cup), 1 stick margarine and beaten egg.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together pumpkin, 3 eggs, brown sugar, 1/4 cup white sugar, cinnamon and milk and pour over cake mixture.
Spread evenly.
Mix reserved cake mix, 1/2 cup white sugar, 1/4 cup margarine and chopped nuts until crumbly and sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Let cool.
Refrigerate.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Blend milk, cherries, lemon juice, pineapple and pecans in mixing bowl.
Pour into pie shell; chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: goulash
directions: Cook egg noodles.
Drain and rinse.
In skillet, brown ground chuck.
Add onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Add tomato soup and water.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Fold in noodles and top with cheese.
Put top on skillet and set off the stove until cheese melts.
Serve with garlic bread and green salad.

title: west virginia biscuits
directions: Mix sugar, yeast and water; let stand 10 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add shortening and cut into flour mixture. Add yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Roll out on floured surface and cut with biscuit cutter.
Let rise 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: my favorite cookies
directions: Roll up and put in refrigerator.
Chill all night.
Bake at 350° on ungreased sheet for 10 minutes.

title: gummy dumplings
directions: Bring stock or broth to boil in a large Dutch oven.
Add spices.
Cut up or tear biscuits into half and drop into boiling liquid.
Add chicken/turkey.
Stir well and reduce heat.
Cover and let cook for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: oven stew
directions: Cut carrots in pieces and combine all ingredients. Do not brown meat.
Put in a 3-quart casserole. Bake covered in a 325° oven for 3 hours.

title: turkey tacos
directions: Brown turkey in nonstick pan.
(Break it up as it browns.) Drain fat if any.
Add spices and water.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: fish
directions: Season fish with tony's. Melt butter in frying pan. Add fish, then onions. Fry 5 minutes on each side until done.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk 5 minutes and stir constantly.
Let bubble rapidly.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients 1 at a time in order.
Stir until thick.
Pour in buttered pan, 9 x 13-inch.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan very well.
Put chicken on top of rice. Mix together the soups and water and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, uncovered.

title: chicken chili
directions: Cover chicken with water (may add onion and celery to flavor broth) and cook 1 hour or until done, but not overdone.
Remove chicken from broth (reserve broth); cool slightly.
Discard skin and bones.
Cut or tear chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Heat oil in large, heavy pot.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook 3 minutes
over low heat.
Stir in chili powder, cumin, curry powder, oregano, allspice and pepper flakes.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
If mixture is too dry add 1/2 cup broth.
Add sweet peppers and mushrooms. Cook, covered, 8 minutes.
Add chicken, tomatoes, kidney beans, 2 cups broth, lemon juice, 2 tablespoons parsley and black pepper. Simmer, uncovered, over low heat for 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add salt to taste and remaining parsley.
More chicken broth can be added until you reach the desired consistency.
Serve in bowls with a large spoonful of white or brown rice.
Garnish with yogurt and chives or green onions, if desired.

title: pork and beans for a big crowd
directions: Brown meat.
Stir in everything else.
Bake in oven at 400° for 30 minutes.
Can also be put in kettle and cooked over campfire.

title: lasagna my way
directions: Brown meat and pour grease into a small container.
In a good size skillet, mix the meat with spaghetti sauce (use 2 jars if you want it really thick, but the final product may be runny), cottage cheese and mushrooms.

title: easy goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off fat.
Add tomato soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes, crushed garlic and red pepper.
Let simmer while you cook the noodles.
Drain noodles and mix together.

title: new orleans bread pudding(with custard sauce)
directions: *If bread is not stale enough, sprinkle with water and put in oven for a few minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook ground meat and onions in oil (about 5 minutes).
Add next 4 ingredients.
Stir in flour.
Add 1 cup water and bouillon cube; bring to boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add Kitchen Bouquet. Pour in baking dish.
Prepare Bisquick mix using milk.
Spoon on top of mixture; spread lightly.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes. Add sour cream; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Sift sugar, cocoa and salt together.
Add eggs, butter, milk and vanilla;
mix
thoroughly.
Pour
into
unbaked
pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare stuffing mix according to directions on box.
Combine milk, soup and parsley.
Set aside.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown lightly hamburger and salt.
Add onion, soup and tomatoes; simmer for 15 minutes, then add the oregano, tomato paste, water, brown sugar and vinegar.
Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add cooked spaghetti and serve.

title: raw fruit pie
directions: Put fruit filling in a 9-inch baked pie shell.
Cover with the following syrup:
Crush 1 cup fruit very fine.
Heat sugar with 1/2 cup water until sugar is dissolved.
Add to the crushed fruit. Mix cornstarch with 2 tablespoons water.
Make a smooth paste and add to the strained mixture.
Cook until thick.
Cool slightly; pour over fruit.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: lemon fluff jello dessert
directions: Combine jello, hot water, sugar and grated lemon rind. When cool and syrupy, add 1 large can milk (chilled) and 3 tablespoons lemon juice.
Whip thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Combine sugar, butter, salt, eggs, vinegar, coconut, pecans and raisins until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated 325 degree oven 40 to 45 minutes or until set in center. Cool at least 1 hour before cutting.

title: shell macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done; drain.
Combine soup, vinegar, oil and sugar.
Chop peppers and onion.
Add to mixture.
Add macaroni when cooled.
Let set in refrigerator for several hours to thicken.

title: easy brownies
directions: Cream together the sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grand champion apple pie
directions: For the apples, select Stayman or Granny Smith.
Combine peeled and sliced apples, sugar, pineapple or orange juice and simmer for 6 to 8 minutes.
Combine flour and spices in sifter and sift over boiling mixture.
Cook, stirring 2 minutes longer.
Add vanilla and butter.
Let stand for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Pour into pie pan lined with pastry.
Top with lattice crust.
Bake in a 425° oven for 30 minutes or until pastry is done.

title: beef mushroom loaf
directions: Drain musrhrooms.
Reserve liquid.
Add enough milk to mushroom liquid to make 1/2 cup.
In a mixing bowl, combine liquid, egg, Worcestershire sauce, salt, mustard, pepper and mushrooms.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Shape into a loaf in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Combine catsup and corn syrup.
Brush on meat loaf and bake 15 minutes more.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except 1/2 stick of margarine and potato chips.
Pour into greased casserole.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine; pour over crushed potato chips.
Put on top of potato mixture and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours uncovered.
Serve hot.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Place second pie crust on top.
Crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Crush cereal to measure 1/2 cup.
Stir together with flour, cinnamon and sugar.
Add butter until crumbly.
Place apples in baking dish; top with crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until apples are tender.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil eggs until done 10-12 minutes. Set aside. Peel & cut up when cool.

title: capellini with scallops
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain, reserving 1/2 cup cooking water.
While pasta cooks, heat oil in skillet. Add garlic.
Cook about 3 minutes.
Stir in scallops, parsley, salt and butter.
Cook over medium heat about 5 minutes.
Pour over pasta.
Serve with grated cheese.
Serves 4.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, butter and 1/4 cup sugar.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.
Blend 1 cup sugar into cream cheese. Fold in whipped cream.
Spread over cooled crust.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in frozen berries. When slightly jelled, spread over cream cheese mix. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: snacking sausage
directions: Combine ingredients in a crock-pot and heat.
Stir every now and then.

title: kids' krunchy krazy korn
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Place popcorn on 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
In large saucepan, combine sugar, margarine and corn syrup. Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly; simmer for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda and vanilla. Pour mixture evenly over popcorn; mix well.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes, stirring twice during baking.
Remove from pan immediately.
Cool on waxed paper.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 8 cups.

title: pound cake
directions: In large bowl, beat butter, sugar and eggs (add one at a time) until smooth.
Add flour, baking powder, milk, vanilla and almond extract and beat until smooth.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter and flour (nonstick as well) a 10-inch tube, Bundt pan, 2 loaf pans or mini loaf pans.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours. Check after 45 minutes.
(Knife will be clean when inserted in middle.)
Cool 1 hour in pan.
Freezes extremely well.

title: great-granny's basic cream pie
directions: Options:
Cocoa added for chocolate cream pie.
Coconut added for coconut cream pie.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: In small bowl, mix sugar, flour and cornmeal.
In large bowl, beat eggs, butter, milk, lemon juice, rind and salt.
Add dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit pudding dessert
directions: Batter:
Melt butter in baking dish or baking pan.
Mix dry ingredients:
flour, baking powder, salt and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add enough milk to make thin batter.
Pour batter into baking dish over melted butter.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cut up chicken.
Add 5 cups water, salt, celery, carrot and onion.
Simmer until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken.
Strain broth.
Cube meat.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix and add enough milk to fill 5-quart freezer.
Freeze as any other homemade ice cream.

title: onion pie
directions: Lightly cook onions in butter.
Make crust in pie of crackers. Place onions over crust.
Beat milk, eggs, salt and pepper and pour over onions.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake 30 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: pepper steak
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, mix together tomato soup, tomato sauce, soy sauce, garlic salt and pepper. Add green peppers, onion and steak.
Cook until tender.
Serve over rice, noodles or macaroni. It's delicious!

title: ronald reagan's corned beef hash in bell peppers
directions: Five minutes before serving, drop raw egg in top of each pepper.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Return to oven until egg has set.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill. Serve over fresh green salad.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and let stand 2 hours.
Mold into balls and roll in finely chopped nuts or sprinkle with paprika or roll in chopped parsley.
For this amount of cheese, use 2 teaspoons each of garlic and celery salt and about 2 tablespoons of the sauces.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not overcook. Slowly pour mixture of cream of coconut and condensed milk over hot cake.
You may punch MANY holes with a toothpick so mixture is absorbed by cake.
When cake is cooled, frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Cake is better if prepared a couple of days in advance.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffing balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine potatoes, bread cubes, onion, celery leaves, parsley, butter, salt and pepper.
In small bowl, mix eggs and flour; stir in milk.
Pour over potato mixture and mix well. Shape in fist size balls.
Place in large cake pan 8 1/2 x 13-inch.
Spray pan with Pam.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crock-pot meatballs
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until cranberry sauce is smooth. Pour over meatballs in crock-pot.
Cook 3 to 5 hours on medium or low.

title: cabbage, pea and peanut salad
directions: Chop cabbage medium-fine, enough to make 4 to 5 cups.
Drain peas well and chill.
Combine cabbage, peas and peanuts.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add mayonnaise.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: frozen loaf bread coffee cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Place nuts or raisins on bottom of pan. Place bread pieces in pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and pudding mix on top of bread.
Cut butter into pieces and add to top of bread. Let rise overnight for breakfast or make at noon for evening meal.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: one hour yeast rolls
directions: Heat milk in a saucepan until warm.
Mix together until smooth sugar, shortening and salt.
Stir the warm milk into creamed mixture.
Add 1 yeast cake (crumbled), egg and flour.
Beat with a spoon until batter is smooth.
Cover and let rise for 30 minutes. Push down and shape into rolls.
Let rise again for 15 minutes. Bake in a 425° oven for 12 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen rolls.

title: pie crust
directions: In saucepan, bring to boil for one minute all ingredients. Pour over 2 cups flour in pie tin.
Stir with spoon until moist. Knead into a ball and press out into pan with your fingers.

title: irish cinnamon potatoes
directions: Beat butter or margarine with corn syrup until blended, then work in the remaining ingredients and knead well.
Pinch off pieces just a bit smaller than walnuts and roll them between the palm of your hands.
With your thumb, flatten one side slightly, then make a few dents with a toothpick so the balls resemble little potato eyes.
Sprinkle a platter or piece of wax paper with cinnamon and roll potatoes until coated.
Be sure to cover dish with plastic wrap to minimize drying out.
Makes about 1 pound of candy.

title: mystery buns
directions: Melt butter.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Unroll crescent rolls, dip marshmallow in melted butter, then in sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Start at large end of roll and wrap marshmallow up. Make sure all the seams are pinched together.
Dip in melted butter.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add other ingredients and roll out very thin.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: no beans about it chili
directions: Brown ground pork; drain grease. Brown hamburger; drain grease. Combine pork and hamburger in food processor to mince. Put all of the ingredients with minced meat into crock-pot. Cook 4 hours on high, then 2 hours on low.

title: watermelon dessert
directions: Line bowl with softened lime sherbet.
Then mix chocolate chips and strawberry ice cream together.
Put in bowl already lined with sherbet and freeze.
Take out and cut for a refreshing dessert.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl until light and fluffy, about 2 minutes.
Add oil and vanilla; beat until thickened, approximately 2 minutes longer.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; add to creamed mixture, alternately with apples and walnuts, beating well after each addition.
Beat at medium speed 3 minutes.
Turn batter into well greased and lightly floured 8 1/2-inch fluted pan.
Bake in 350° oven 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.

title: baked stuffed muskrat with carrots and onions
directions: Soak the muskrat overnight in salted water.
Cook the potatoes and mash them with margarine.
Mix in salt, pepper, savory, garlic powder and chopped celery.
Stuff the muskrat with this mixture and sew it up.
Salt and pepper the muskrat.
Place on a rack in a roasting pan.
Place carrots and onions around the muskrat, bacon strips across the back and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Pour 2 cups hot water over the muskrat and cook for about 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put 3 cups berries in baked pie shell.
Crush 1 cup berries in small pan and add water.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Strain and add enough water to make 1 cup.
Mix with sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until smooth and clear.
Remove from heat and let cool slightly (about 5 minutes).
Pour glaze over berries in pie shell.

title: glorified pork chops
directions: Cook chops in hot oil over medium heat with onions until browned on both sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup and water. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until chops are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Put into a large bowl and mix well.
Store in a gallon jug. Use 1/3 cup mix and finish filling cup with hot water (or use 4 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup).
Keep jug capped.
Can be stored in freezer.

title: crockpot turkey
directions: Wash turkey breast and dry with paper towels.
Rub olive oil over entire surface.
Place turkey breast in crock-pot, sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef, then add all remaining ingredients into a large (6-quart kettle).
Cook on low heat until vegetables are cooked well.

title: chili low calorie
directions: Brown onions, pepper and meat in skillet.
Put in pot and add tomatoes and seasonings; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add beans last 5 minutes.
Serves 8. Has 250 calories, 10 fat grams; food exchanges equal 2 meats, 1 bread, 1 vegetable.

title: ratatouille
directions: Heat olive oil in a large skillet; add garlic and onions. Cook until onions are tender, but not brown.
Layer remaining vegetables in the skillet, sprinkling each layer with monosodium glutamate, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, over low heat about 20 minutes.
Uncover skillet; continue cooking at a simmer until most of the liquid has evaporated, about 15 minutes or less.
Serve hot or cold.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top before serving. Serves 6 to 8.
This keeps well in the refrigerator for days.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients, except chicken.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Place chicken in shallow baking pan.
Brush with sauce.
Bake at 375° about an hour.
Continue to baste occasionally with sauce while baking.
Simmer remaining sauce for 10 minutes more and pass with chicken.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together and cook on High for 4 minutes in microwave.
Stir and cook on High 4 more minutes.
Add butter or margarine and vanilla. Stir and cook 2 more minutes on High.
Remove from microwave and add baking soda.
Stir quickly and pour onto greased cookie sheet to cool.

title: green tomato crisp
directions: Soak tomato slices in the lime water, made by stirring 3 cups garden lime into 2 gallons water, for 24 hours.
Drain, then rinse well under running water.
Soak for 4 hours in fresh cold water, changing water every hour.
Drain.

title: oatmeal icebox cookies
directions: Mix in order and form in rolls.
Chill and slice.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips and melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Mix potato chips and 1/4 cup margarine and spread on top of casserole.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, egg, salt and Crisco.
Add bananas and sour cream.
Then add flour, soda and baking powder.
Then add chopped nuts. Let sit 10 minutes in pan before baking.
Makes 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix crumbs, powdered sugar, 2 cups nuts and cocoa.
Add corn syrup and rum.
Mix well.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Roll half in granulated sugar and remainder in 1 cup nuts.
Moisten cut sides of cherry halves with corn syrup and press one on each sugar coated rum ball.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: cornmeal mush
directions: Put water and salt in top section of double boiler.
Set directly on range and bring to boiling point.
Pour cornmeal slowly into water while constantly stirring.
Cook 3 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts, debone and cube meat.
Mix soups with sour cream.
Add meat to soup mixture. Pour into casserole dish. Crush crackers.
Mix with melted butter.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top of casserole.
Sprinkle with poppy seed. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve over hot, fluffy rice.

title: skillet turkey lasagna(serves 4)
directions: Brown turkey with onions in a nonstick 10-inch skillet.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Then add the tomato sauce, tomatoes, the other 1/4 cup water, the seasonings and Parmesan, the Ricotta and the noodles.
Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until the noodles are tender.
Sometimes, I add mushrooms or chopped green pepper. Approximately 330 calories per serving.

title: sausage and potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Boil in water until almost done. Brown sausage with onions and drain.
Cook broccoli until almost done.
Layer in large casserole dish in order: potatoes, sausage, onions, broccoli and cheese.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Great!

title: joe's barbecue shrimp
directions: Clean and dehead shrimp.
Slice bacon in half.
Combine Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and butter in a small saucepan. Bring to a simmer over low heat.
Wrap 1 bacon slice around 1 shrimp and secure with a toothpick and place on skewer.
Season with Nature's Seasons and place on grill.
Baste with sauce several times.
Turn skewers over and continue to baste with sauce until shrimp are done.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix and bake in slow oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Crush crackers finely and add melted butter and sugar to them. Press mixture firmly into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Reserve some of crumb mixture for garnish.
Blend thawed orange juice and milk.
Stir in Cool Whip and oranges.
Fold in.
Do not beat. Pour mixture over crumb crust.
Top with reserved crumbs. Refrigerate or freeze until serving time.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Cream cheese and sugar together.
Add peanut butter and milk. Beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Turn into crust and chill 6 hours or longer before cutting.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Gently fold into all other ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup mayonnaise and stir, adding as much as you need to make it the consistency you want.
Add salt and pepper to your taste.
Chill 1 hour before serving.
Serves 6.

title: boiled chicken and rice
directions: Boil a medium cut up chicken in about 3 1/2 cups of salted to taste water until almost done.
Add rice and some black pepper. Cook, uncovered, about 20 minutes.
Serve hot in bowls with lots of black pepper.

title: cream cheese cups
directions: Put muffin cup wrappers in muffin pans.
Place vanilla wafer in bottom of each.
Fill each 3/4 full with mixture.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Top with cherry pie filling, pineapple, peach, whatever!
These are great!

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle 1 cup of buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°; let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook
potatoes,
onions and salt to taste until tender. Stir in
mushroom
and celery soup until smooth. Then stir in sour cream.
Good warmed over.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed. Mix in evaporated milk, sugar, whole milk and vanilla until sugar dissolves.
Pour into freezer can.
Freeze according to general operating directions.
Makes approximately 1 gallon.

title: quick corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1
hour.

title: quick peach dessert
directions: Combine Bisquick and sugar in a 9-inch square pan. With fork, cut in margarine. Stir in milk; add peaches. Drizzle peach juice over top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fried pie pastry
directions: Sift and measure flour.
Add baking soda.
Sift again; cut in shortening until looks like meal.
Blend in sweet milk.

title: home-style banana bread(sugar-free)
directions: Beat together mashed banana, oil, eggs and water until creamy. Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and spices.
Beat well. Stir in chopped walnuts.
Spoon batter into an oiled and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger well.
Add onion, green pepper and spices. Use a good bit of garlic powder.
Add soup, tomato paste and water.
Cook the sauce for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add water when it thickens.
When you think it is about done, allow it to thicken without adding any more water.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, then add squash.
Save part of cheese to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water.
Shred the cheese.
Put minced onion and butter in top of a double boiler.
When butter has melted, stir in the flour, mustard, salt and pepper.
Slowly stir in the milk and 3/4 of cheese until the cheese has melted.

title: chicken breasts orange
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Place on baking dish.
Sprinkle with soup mix.
Spoon orange juice over chicken. Cover dish with foil and bake 1 hour.
Uncover; baste and cook another 15 or 20 minutes.

title: cream-style corn
directions: Cut corn from cob, cutting only about 1/2 of kernel; scrape cob.
Put corn in pan and add milk, butter and salt and pepper. Cook slowly on low heat, stirring often as this will scorch very easily.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes after it comes to a boil.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In order written, mix all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: macaroni and cheese and spam casserole
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package except using 3/4 cup milk. Add peas and soup and mix well. Pour into 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish. Arrange luncheon meat squares in checkerboard pattern. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread crumbs in 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Blend in rest of the ingredients.
Place dish in pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: crispix sugar
directions: Melt butter or margarine and brown sugar together.
Pour over Crispix and pecans; coat thoroughly.
Place on two cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: In large saucepan, put 1/2 cup oil and heat slowly.
Add tomatoes, corn and liquid from corn.
Add cornmeal mix and stir. Cover and cook slowly for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In a frypan, put 1/2 cup oil.
Saute garlic and onion; add meat and brown with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Combine cornmeal mixture.
Add olives.
Bake mixture in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: almond shortbread
directions: Place almonds in a food processor, process until finely ground. Set aside.
Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Stir in almond extract.
Combine ground almonds, flour and salt; gradually add to butter mixture, beating at low speed until blended.
Roll dough to 1/2 inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch round cutter or Christmas cookie cutter.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 275 degrees for 45 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheets.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Yields 17 cookies.

title: irish potato salad
directions: Cube potatoes and mix with seeds, vinegar, sugar and salt. Add other ingredients.
Best made a day before planning to serve. Serves 8.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix well and turn in well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry bonbon cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy; gradually add all other ingredients.
Shape into 24 balls.
Press each ball around a cherry.
(Cover cherry completely.)
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 minutes.
Transfer to wire rack.
Cool.
Dust cookies with powdered sugar and drizzle with cherry glaze.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well except the Ritz crackers and margarine.
Put into casserole dish. Top casserole with the crackers.
Dot crackers with the margarine. Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add oil and mix well.
Add eggs one at a time; blend well and add carrots.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
This is a moist, delicious cake.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Arrange fruit on a mixture of melted butter and brown sugar. Make a cake batter of your choice or yellow packaged cake mix and pour over the fruit mixture.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: cowboy casserole
directions: Mix meat, beans and rice and bake for 25 minutes at 350°. Top with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Serve with lettuce, sour cream, taco sauce, etc.

title: new orleans chili
directions: In large saucepan, combine tomatoes, tomato sauce, meat, onion, pepper, chili powder, cumin and cayenne pepper.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in kidney beans and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Garnish with shredded Cheddar cheese, if desired. Serves 6.

title: brandy slush
directions: Boil 7 cups water with sugar.
Boil 2 cups water with the tea bags for 4 minutes.
Let cool. Add the lemonade and orange juice. Add brandy. Freeze.
When ready to serve, scoop into a glass and pour ginger ale over it.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; cream until smooth.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix.
Add nuts and 1/2 cup of chocolate chips; mix.
Spread in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread remaining chocolate chips on top.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 5 minutes.
Using a knife, make a grid through the melted chips on top.
Bake further for 15 minutes.
The brownies may look raw, but are cooked when brown at the edges.
Cut when cooled.
Yield:
16 brownies.

title: chicken zucchini casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Drain fat and discard.
In small amount of water, cook whole zucchini.
When tender, chop finely. Combine cheese and crumbs in large bowl.
Set aside 2 tablespoons of cheese crumb mixture.
Add chicken, seasonings and chopped zucchini to cheese crumb mix in large bowl.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
In separate bowl, beat together yolks and milk.
Stir into chicken mixture.
Gently fold in egg whites.
Turn into greased shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs mixed with melted butter and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat the milk in a pot with the 1/2 cup of butter until the butter is melted.
Put eggs in a bowl and mix. Add to the milk in the pot the sugar, eggs and the cinnamon.
Break into small pieces the loaf of bread in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Pour the mixture from the pot over the bread and mix.
Bake at 325° until golden brown, about 40 minutes.

title: no fry doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, sugar, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, eggs, shortening and 2 cups flour.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Stir in remaining flour until smooth.
Cover; let rise in warm place 50 to 60 minutes.
Dough will be soft to handle.
Roll lightly in flour, then roll to 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Place 2 to 3 inches apart on cooking sheet.
Melt butter or margarine; brush on them.
Cover and let rise until double.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Butter again and glaze to choice.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Mix the gelatin, cornstarch and cold water in a saucepan.
Add boiling water.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil; remove from heat.
When mixture is cool (not solid), add strawberries.
Pour into baked crust and chill until solid.
Before serving, top with frozen whipped topping spread evenly over pie.

title: peach punch
directions: Mix together puree, water and juices.
Immediately before serving, add ginger ale and champagne and float peach slices in bowl as garnish.
If punch starts to lose its color, add red and yellow food coloring, a drop at a time.
Serves 50.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend together first 5 ingredients.
When well blended, fold in last 3 ingredients.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.
Serve cold with crackers.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Chop lettuce, celery, bell pepper, onion and green onion in amounts desired for size salad.
Layer in order of ingredients. Spread mayonnaise over vegetables in the desired amount of thickness you want.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: quick rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until moistened.
Drop 1 tablespoon mixture into muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: In double boiler, melt butter and onion.
Gradually add milk and shrimp.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Slowly stir in light cream. Heat, but do not boil.
Add sherry, parsley or chives, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Blend well.

title: chocolate sweetheart cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat together cream cheese, 3/4 cup butter and vanilla.
Alternately beat in sugar and 1/4 cup of milk. Stir in 4 squares of melted chocolate.
Remove 3 1/2 cups to small pitcher for frosting; apply seal and chill.

title: steak and potato bake
directions: Peel, slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Cover in cold water. Cut meat into serving size pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Sear meat on both sides in hot skillet.
Place meat in large casserole dish.
Top with potatoes, onions and mushrooms. Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Combine with tomato juice, salt, pepper, oregano
and parsley.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until meat and potatoes are tender.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together and slowly pour in milk. When smooth, fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: icebox coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix by directions on the box.
Add 1 package of frozen coconut and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While the cake bakes, add the sugar to the milk and let it sit.
When the cake is done, prick it extra well with a big fork and pour the milk and sugar mixture over the hot cake.
Let it cool completely.
Mix 1/2 package coconut into Cool Whip and spread on cake.
Top with the rest of coconut.
Keep in the refrigerator.
Better the next day or the next!!!!

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Put about 1 cup flour in bag.
Put 1/4 to 1/2 oleo in baking dish and put on low heat in oven until melted.
Place chicken in flour and seasonings and shake until covered.
Place in baking dish and cook 1 hour on 425°.
Turn once.

title: cary's brown sugar pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla and beat well.
Add butter. Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 325° about 45 minutes or until custard is firmly set.

title: supreme rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish.
Cover tightly and microwave 5 minutes on High.
Stir and microwave 5 additional minutes on 50% power.
Let stand several minutes before serving.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Mix all together.
Spread on a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dip for bagels
directions: Mix ingredients.
Let sit overnight.
Cut up bagels.
Better with variety of bagels (wheat, rye and onion).

title: quick and easy fajitas
directions: In a medium large Teflon frypan, brown meat in very tiny amount of oil (or spray pan with Pam).
Add onion and saute until soft. Add bell pepper; stir a minute and then add entire can tomatoes. Break tomatoes into small pieces.
Add fajita seasoning.
Stir occasionally over medium heat until tomato juice has cooked down and mixture is a thick gravylike consistency.
Serves approximately 4.

title: lentil soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Combine butter, egg, lemon peel, buttermilk and flour mixture. Fold in blueberries. Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Top muffins with lemon glaze.

title: rice casserole
directions: In Dutch oven, put 2 cups rice with water, mushroom soup and bouillon cubes and let come to a boil.
Lower heat and let simmer for 15 minutes.
While doing the above, have hamburg sauteing in pan until lightly brown.
Add it to the rice mixture when done. You may add peas, green beans or chopped spinach while cooking rice or have as a side dish.
Be creative.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Combine hamburger, onion, green pepper and celery, cooking until browned.
Drain grease and add remaining ingredients, simmering for 30 minutes.
Combine sauce mixture with cooked mostaccioli noodles until noodles are evenly covered.
May top with Parmesan cheese.

title: meat balls in mushroom gravy
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together; form into balls.
In a large skillet, brown meat balls on all sides.
Cover with the soup and milk.
Let simmer 1/2 to 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt stick of butter, then mix in bowl flour, 2 cups sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour over butter in pan, but don't mix together.
Then in saucepan, put fruit and 1 cup sugar, if needed.
Heat until hot.
Then pour over batter mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add egg yolks and melted chocolate.
Add dry ingredients, which have been sifted together three times, alternately with cold water.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in two 9-inch cake pans or a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° until it springs back when touched with finger, about 35 minutes.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Bake the lean spareribs in a shallow pan for 1 1/4 hours. Drain off fat.
Pour a sauce of the rest of the ingredients over and bake 45 minutes longer at 350°.

title: chocolate marvel pie
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients in top of double boiler.
Stir when melted.
Cool slightly.
Add vanilla and egg yolks beaten in separately, beat well after adding the yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into baked 9-inch crust.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Place milk, oleo and sugar in saucepan; boil to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme and nuts.
Pour in buttered pan.

title: strawberry apple slush
directions: Blend together strawberries with apple juice in a blender until smooth.
Pour in a glass and garnish with a sprig of fresh mint.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add all of the ingredients in a mixing bowl. Mix.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: polynesian hot dog
directions: Combine syrup from pineapple chunks with water.
Add vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch and soy sauce.
Set aside.
Saute onion and celery in oil until hot, not brown.
Add franks, pineapple and sauce mixture.
Heat, stirring for 3 to 4 minutes until thick. Add green pepper (if desired).
Heat.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: billy goat cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices. Add dry mixture to egg mixture with sour milk.
Blend well.
Add nuts and dates.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
7 to 8 dozen.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.
Very good.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Heat sauce and dip tortillas in hot sauce.
Add 2 tablespoons of cheese mixture and roll.
Pour sauce over all and put grated cheese on top.
May also use chopped onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: quick caramel coffee ring
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In small saucepan, melt margarine.
Coat bottom and sides of ungreased 12 cup fluted tube pan with 2 tablespoons of melted margarine.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons of the pecans over bottom of prepared pan.
Add remaining pecans, brown sugar and water to the remaining margarine; heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Separate dough into 20 biscuits; cut each biscuit in half and shape into a ball.
Place 20 dough balls in bottom of prepared pan.
Drizzle half of the caramel sauce over the dough balls.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Invert immediately onto waxed paper and remove from pan.
Serves 10.

title: french kraut
directions: Put first 4 ingredients through food chopper.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: breakfast cheesecake
directions: Put cottage cheese, eggs, vanilla, salt and sweetener in blender.
Whirl at high speed until smooth and creamy.
Pour into shell and bake in preheated 275° oven for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and let cheesecake cool in oven for 1 hour.
Cover and chill before serving.
One-fifth slice = 108 calories.
For fun sometime, add a small can crushed pineapple, well drained.
Omit lemon juice.

title: christmas rocks
directions: Chop cherries, pineapple and pecans.
Pour orange juice over fruit and let stand 1 hour.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 c. flour over fruit & nut mixture.
Mix eggs, butter, sugar, 1 1/2 c. flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Add fruit mixture and mix well.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees until edges are brown.
Cookies will be soft.

title: cocoa frosting
directions: Cook over medium heat. Boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over your favorite plain cake cooked in a sheet pan.
Punch holes in cake so frosting will soak in it.

title: caramel corn
directions: Placed popped corn in 2 ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pans. In heavy saucepan, combine next 4 ingredients.
Bring to slow boil, continue cooking over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in soda (will become foamy).
Pour over corn and stir until well coated.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool.
If storing, use plastic bag or airtight can.

title: batter dip for fried vegetables
directions: Cut up your favorite vegetables; dip in mixture and deep fry. Great for onion rings and boneless chicken breast strips.

title: 5 minutes from can to man soup
directions: Brown and drain meat; add onions and pepper and simmer. Add next cans of Ranch Style beans, minestrone soup and tomatoes. Simmer and top with grated cheese.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix ingredients.
Add pecans and stir. Put in oven and turn heat back to 300°.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Let cook before cutting.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, salt, pepper, Cheez Whiz and 1/2 of the oleo. Place in casserole dish.
Mix remaining oleo with crackers and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes until done or brown.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and cook until vegetables are tender.
Add 1 cup milk, thickened with 1 tablespoon flour.
Put 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese in.
Stir until melted.

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Spread filling over crackers and cover with another layer of whole crackers and press down lightly.
Cover with icing.
Cover and let set in refrigerator overnight before cutting into sticks.

title: broccoli pecan casserole
directions: Combine first seven ingredients.
Put into greased casserole. Top with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven fried vegetables
directions: In a small bowl combine bread crumbs and oil, then add Parmesan.
In a different small bowl, combine egg and water.
Dip vegetables in egg, then crumb mixture.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until crust is crisp.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix rice, soups and water in large casserole dish.
Place chicken on top of mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: 1 bowl pineapple cake
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon lush(serves:  approximately 8 to 10)
directions: Mix pudding and milk well until thick; spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: skillet apple pie(breakfast pie)
directions: Grease well two 9-inch iron skillets or two 9-inch pie pans. Divide apples between the two pans.
Set aside.

title: mexican corn
directions: Mix mushrooms, corn, picante sauce and oleo together.
Place in baking dish and bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: banana sheet cake
directions: Combine all items in large bowl and beat 4 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool slightly.
Pour banana glaze over top.
Let mellow for a day or two.
Makes very moist cake.

title: spanish cream cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy peach crisp
directions: Place sliced peaches in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until topping is golden brown.

title: chocolate butterfinger ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients and freeze in old-fashioned ice cream freezer.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix salad dressing and cream cheese until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Serve with vegetable dippers and assorted crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: russian baked butter balls
directions: Beat together sugar and butter.
Gradually add flour.
Stir in vanilla, salt and nuts.
Shape into balls.
Place on an ungreased pan.
Slightly flatten tops.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple cinnamon puffs
directions: Boil sugar, water and red food coloring to a syrup, about 5 minutes.
Peel and thinly slice apples; place in a greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Pour syrup over apples.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening; stir in milk.
Drop 12 spoonfuls of dough on top of apples.
Make a dent in the middle of each.
Mix the melted butter, 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon; add to the dents.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chili dip-southwestern
directions: Stir cheese, mayonnaise, half of the olives, half of the peppers, garlic and hot sauce.
Place in a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake about 20 minutes, uncovered.
Do not overbake!
Sprinkle with the chopped tomato, balance of olives and chili peppers.
Serve with pita chips or corn chips.

title: cranberry-orange pork steaks
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet; brown steaks. Season both sides with salt. Stir together relish, orange juice and nutmeg. Spread on steaks. Cover tightly; simmer 1 hour or until tender. Serve each steak with orange slice.

title: seafood primavera
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Bring the vegetables and water to a boil in a medium saucepan.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 3 minutes.
Drain.
Add milk, soup, crabmeat, margarine, garlic salt and basil.
Stir in cooked rice. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender.
Add water and bouillon cubes; bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve cubes.
Add noodles and cook, uncovered, for 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add broccoli and garlic.
Cook for 4 minutes; add rest of ingredients and cook until broccoli is done.

title: sea shell shrimp salad
directions: Cook shell macaroni according to package directions; drain well.
Cool.
(Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.)

title: old fashioned corn chowder
directions: Saute bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan.
Fry onion in bacon fat until soft.
Stir in flour.
Add milk slowly, stirring until thick.
Cook potatoes and corn in water until potatoes are tender. Add onion gravy to potato mixture.
Add bacon and seasoning. Serve hot.
Stir over flame until well mixed and mixture boils. Serves 6 to 8.

title: party ryes
directions: Combine mayo, green onion, bacon and Parmesan cheese.
Spread on party rye bread (appetizer loaf by Pepperidge Farm).
Broil until mixture bubbles (approximately 1 to 2 minutes).
Watch carefully!

title: mock raspberry jam
directions: Mix tomatoes and sugar in a saucepan.
Cook for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in gelatin.
Bring to a rolling boil. Cook for 7 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Spoon into sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace; seal with 2-piece lids.
Yields 50 servings.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Put cheese with soup in pan to melt (save some cheese for top).
Combine soup and cheese with mayo, eggs and onion.
Add to broccoli.
Mix together and put in 9-inch baking dish that has been greased.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Combine melted butter and stuffing mix.
Place on top of cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peaches and cheesecake
directions: Combine the cream cheese, sugar and peach juice.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 12 plus.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water; cook until mixture spins a thread. Pour in peanuts.
Cook until light brown.
Add salt, butter, soda and stir.
Mixture will foam.
Pour immediately on buttered aluminum foil.
Let spread.
Best stored in glass containers. Will freeze.

title: white chocolate cheesecake(makes 8 servings. prep time: 10 minutes.)
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer until blended. Add eggs and blend well.
Stir in chocolate chips. Pour into crust. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: zucchini lemon bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf pan.
Heat oven to 350°F.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery.
Combine all other ingredients. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cut bacon into 1/4's and cook and drain.
Mix apples and sugar together. Spread mixture into bottom of a greased 12 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon over apples.
Beat Bisquick, milk and eggs until smooth.
Pour over top of ingredients in pan. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean. Makes a lot!

title: refrigerator cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add cold water.
Set aside at room temperature.
Mix and bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan as directed on package.
While cake is still warm, make 1/2-inch holes, especially at the edges.
Cool, then pour Jell-O in the holes and place cake in refrigerator.
In chilled bowl, blend remaining ingredients and beat until stiff and fluffy.
Frost cake.

title: nell smith's strawberry bread
directions: Sift together first four ingredients.
Mix together sugar, oil and eggs.
Add strawberries to sugar, oil and egg mixture, alternately with dry ingredients, until just blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ginger ale, and chill.
Add chilled ginger ale at serving time and float pineapple or lime sherbet on top.
Serves 24.

title: saffron rice
directions: Heat chicken stock until warm.
Remove from heat; add saffron and leave to soak for 20 minutes.
In medium skillet, heat oil and 1 tablespoon butter.
Add onion and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until soft but not browned.
Add rice and cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned.
Pour in saffron-flavored stock and add salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer on low 20 minutes.
Let rice stand, covered, 10 minutes.
Using large fork, carefully stir in remaining butter and taste for seasoning.
Serve immediately.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Serve with lettuce and add paprika for color.

title: chick pea dip (middle eastern recipe)(hommos bi tahimi)
directions: Combine ingredients in blender or food processor at high speed until smooth.
Add extra lemon, salt, garlic as desired. Pour into small bowl.
Garnish with parsley, sprinkle paprika and cumin powder lightly and serve.
Delicious with Syrian bread or crackers.
Veggies work also.
If you prefer thinner dip add liquid from chick peas.

title: sopa de pan en cazuela(columbian bread pot soup)
directions: Toast and butter the bread.
Break into large pieces and put several pieces in the bottom of each individual bowl.
Drop whole uncooked egg in each bowl.
Dissolve the bouillon cubes in 4 cups of boiling water and immediately pour the boiling liquid on top of the eggs.
Sprinkle generously with grated cheese to taste.
Put a slice of Swiss cheese on top of each bowl.
Put bowls in the oven under the broiler until Swiss cheese begins to melt.
Garnish with parsley or coriander (or both).
The native dish in Colombia is served in earthenware bowls.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms, then beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough into 10 to 12 mounds on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix melted margarine and garlic powder and brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheets.
Serve warm.

title: the very best cake icing
directions: Melt water, marshmallows and butter or margarine over low heat until marshmallows are melted.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Add chocolate bits and beat until smooth.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: fruit punch
directions: Put preceding into clean gallon jug and finish filling jug with ginger ale.
Chill overnight.
Makes 32 punch cups.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine marshmallows and strawberry juice in saucepan; heat slowly until smooth and fluffy.
Chill.
Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Blend in fruit and marshmallow mixture. Fold in whipped cream.
Place in refrigerator tray and freeze.

title: pretzel salad
directions: In a bowl combine crushed pretzels, sugar, and melted margarine.
Press into bottom of 9 X 13-inch pan or baking dish.

title: tortilla pie
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Add chili powder, tomato sauce and 1/4 cup water.
In a greased bowl, lay down first tortilla on bottom of bowl.
Add about 1 1/2 tablespoons of meat mixture (spread around very sparingly).
Add another tortilla and repeat the same procedure until you've done about 8 or so levels. Last level should be meat mixture.
Pour 1/2 cup water all over top and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cook in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: meat pie
directions: Cut ham in 1/2 inch cubes; slice salami and pepperoni in very small pieces.
Put all meat together in saucepan.
Cover with water and boil slowly for ten minutes.
Drain.
Cut cheese in small cubes; add grated cheese and pepperoni and mix with meat.
Place meat and cheese mixture in baking dish.
Firm mixture down.
Break eggs in bowl; add milk and beat by hand until well blended.
Pour over meat.
Eggs should cover the meat.
If it seems too dry add more egg.
Bake at 400° until light brown.
Very good cut in squares and sent in lunch box.

title: ham and cheese biscuits(low-fat and sodium)
directions: Coat a medium-size nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add ham; saute 3 minutes.
Combine ham, flour, cheese, baking powder and red pepper in bowl.
Add milk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moist.
Drop batter by heaping tablespoonfuls onto baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 22 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cut cooked, deboned chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Mix together chicken, soup, chicken broth, savory and basil in large saucepan; bring just to boil.
Stir in peas, carrots and mushrooms.
Turn into 11 x 7-inch baking dish (2-quart casserole). Mix together flour and buttermilk; add melted margarine.
Spread on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes, until top is golden brown.

title: "pink stuff"(fruit salad)
directions: Refrigerate everything except bananas.
Mix pie filling, condensed milk and pineapple together.
Fold in fruit and fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Makes at least 3 quarts.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/4-inch thick; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Coat tomato slices with cornmeal.
Add to hot bacon drippings in skillet over medium heat.
Cook until brown on both sides; drain. Serves 3.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Cook broccoli for 3 minutes. Salt broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: easy quick sweet pickles(made from dill pickles)
directions: Cut dills in chunks; add all of the above ingredients in bowl. May heat vinegar and sugar with a little of the pickle juice to dissolve. Place in refrigerator, covered and stir occasionally for 24 hours.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan; add cocoa and mix well.
Add boiling water gradually, stirring constantly.
Heat to boiling; add sugar and syrup, stirring until dissolved.
Simmer for 5 minutes; add vanilla.
Serve hot.

title: cashew triangles
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugars, butter, vanilla and egg yolks. Stir in flour and salt.
Press dough in ungreased rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with floured hands.
Beat egg white and water; brush over dough.
Sprinkle with cashews and press them lightly into dough.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cut into 3-inch squares.
Cut each square diagonally in half.
Immediately remove from pan and cool.
Drizzle with chocolate.
Let stand about 2 hours or until chocolate is set.
Makes 24 cookies. Contains 115 calories each.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fry 3 slices bacon crisp and crumble over the mixture.
Cook 4 to 8 hours in slow cooker.

title: flan
directions: Sprinkle sugar in round cake pan.
Place over medium heat. Caramelize sugar by shaking pan occasionally, until sugar melts and turns a light golden brown.
Cool; combine next 6 ingredients in blender.
Process 15 seconds on high.
Pour over sugar; cover pan with aluminum foil and place into a large shallow pan.
Pour hot water into larger pan to a depth of 1-inch.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until a knife inserted into center comes out clean. Remove pan from water and uncover.
Let cool on rack at least 30 minutes.
Loosen edge with spatula, invert onto a plate.

title: date cake
directions: Stir ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350° or until tested done.
Can be served with whipped topping, ice cream, dusted with confectioners sugar or frosted.

title: garlic cheese rolls
directions: Grate Cheddar, then cream with cream cheese until smooth. Grind pecans and garlic; mix with cheese.
After well mixed, roll into 3 rolls about 1 1/2 inches thick, then roll in chili powder to coat.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix well the butter, sour cream and flavorings.
Add egg yolks, beating one at a time.
Beat in flour, salt and soda.
Fold in frothy egg whites last.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix sour cream and soup.
Stir into the broccoli.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Use a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cranberry loaf(yield: 1 loaf)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: egg white candy
directions: Beat
egg
white
stiff.
Add
brown
sugar, pecans and vanilla.
Drop
on	greased cookie sheet; bake 30 minutes in a 250° oven.	Turn off oven, but do not open door.
Leave for 30 minutes more.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Bowl must be at room temperature.
Combine egg yolks, lemon juice, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper in medium bowl.
Whisk until smooth.
Add half the oil, drop by drop, whisking continuously to incorporate oil thoroughly.
Continue whisking and add remaining oil in slow steady stream.
Thinly slice green onion; mince capers and gherkin.
Fold these and parsley into mayonnaise.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: chinese salad
directions: Combine chopped cabbage and onions; set aside.
Melt butter in skillet; crumble noodles (do not use season packet).
Add almonds; cook, stirring, until lightly browned.
Add sunflower seeds; toss until lightly browned.
Remove from heat; set aside to cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt oleo; add onions and brown.
Add broccoli and cook for 15 minutes.
Add soup and 1/4 can water and cook for 5 minutes more. Remove from heat.
Add Cheez Whiz and rice.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: taco scramble
directions: In a large bowl, mix popped corn and tortilla chips; set aside.
In a small saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Stir in seasoning mix until blended.
Pour seasoned butter over popped corn and chips.
Gently stir until well coated.
Cool slightly before eating.
Store in a large airtight container.

title: blessing pie
directions: Crush gingersnaps and mix with melted margarine.
Pat into a pie plate and bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn, add cucumbers, onion, mayonnaise and sugar. Cover and chill.
Add tomatoes before serving.

title: buttery caramels
directions: Use medium to heavy saucepan.
Combine brown sugar, corn syrup, milk and butter.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil 30 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan; let cool.
Cut into squares and wrap in pieces of waxed paper.

title: steamed artichokes
directions: Remove stems from artichokes so they will stand up. Snap off any leaves that are bruised or loose.
Lay artichoke on its side and cut 1 inch off top.
With scissors, trim each of leaf points. Place them in a large pot standing up.
Spread open tops of artichokes with your hands.
Individually sprinkle each artichoke with a little of each of the seasonings.
Add about 1/2 inch of water in bottom of pan.
Cover and steam for 1 hour.
Artichokes are done when you pull out a leaf easily.
Serve as an appetizer.

title: red potato salad with sour cream and chives
directions: Scrub potatoes (do not peel!!).
Boil potatoes until fork tender.
Drain, dry and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
In a salad bowl, combine potatoes, sour cream, yogurt and chives.
Toss gently to coat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate until chilled. Makes 10 servings.

title: banana split cake
