directions: Mix together 1 stick margarine and crushed graham crackers. Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press it down.
In bowl, combine the other stick of butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix well and spread over graham cracker crust.
Next, layer sliced bananas and then strawberries and top with well drained pineapple. Spread Cool Whip on top of this and sprinkle with pecans and dot with cherries.

title: sausage bean bake
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add kidney beans and pork and beans, then all other ingredients.
Stir until mixed well.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Simmer slow for 2 hours.
After cooked, add 1 cup rum per quart.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter, crumble crackers and soak in butter.
Divide in half.
Place 1/2 of buttered crackers in casserole dish.
Chop chicken and mix together with sour cream and soups.
Pour mixture over crumbs.
Top mixture with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: molasses apple pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and spices.
Pat a little of this in pie crust.
Add some apple slices.
Sprinkle with spice mixture. Continue until pan is full.
Pour molasses over all.
Dot with butter.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 425°.

title: baklava(greek pastry)
directions: You will need 1 (2-inch) deep baking tray approximately 12 x 16-inch.
(I use a jelly roll pan only 1-inch deep.)

title: cabbage cha cha
directions: Shred cabbage.
Chop celery, green pepper and onion very fine. Combine in a large bowl.
Mix Crisco oil, lemon juice and sugar together.
Beat until beads form.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Let marinate in refrigerator until served.

title: homemade macaroons
directions: Mix eggs, water, oil and salt.
Add to flour and knead together.
Put into plastic bag and knead every so often until dough is very smooth.
Roll on wire.
Takes 1/2 hour for cooking.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix
all
dry ingredients together.
Add eggs and corn; mix well.
This
should
be
a medium mixture.	If not, add a little milk.
Fry in deep fat measuring with a teaspoon.
Have grease
on medium or hot fire, just so they will cook all the way without burning.
Constantly turn as they brown.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix well and shape into balls 1-inch.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes, do not brown.
Roll in sugar while warm.
Let cool and roll in sugar again.

title: perky punch
directions: Combine juices, water and sugar in a 30-cup percolator.
Place cloves and cinnamon in basket and perk.
Makes a great cold night drink for a gathering.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Scrape squash and cut into slices. Cook with chopped onion in small amount of water 10 to 15 minutes, drain and add soup and sour cream, mix well. Put into buttered 2 quart casserole dish, cover with cracker crumbs and grated cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mom brinkley's carrot cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and carrots.
Add to dry sifted ingredients. Mix thoroughly.
Makes 2 thick or 3 medium layers. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 3 layers.

title: chocolate-coconut cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: breakfast cheese danish
directions: Combine cheese and spices in blender or beat well with mixer. Spread on toast and place in broiler until warmed (or microwave). You'll love this with apple slices, crushed pineapple, cinnamon and nutmeg on top of cheese.

title: sweet pea salad
directions: Drain peas; mix all ingredients.

title: s'mores
directions: Outdoor S'mores:
Toast marshmallow over fire until golden brown.
Place between 2 graham crackers and six Hershey milk chocolate squares.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a casserole dish.

title: cream puffs
directions: Boil water; add butter.
Let butter melt.
After melted, add flour; stir into ball.
Take off heat, place in bowl and let cool. Add eggs, one at a time.
Then spoon out dough into small balls on cookie sheet.
Cook for 30 minutes, until golden brown, at 350°.
Stuff with cream and add powdered sugar on top.

title: hamburger macaroni casserole
directions: Preheat electric skillet to 360°.
Add shortening.
When melted, add onion; fry, stirring, until just beginning to brown. Add meat; fry until browned.
Pour off excess fat.
Add tomatoes, celery, green peppers and cooked macaroni.
Bring to a boil. Cover; turn dial to about 220°.
Simmer about 35 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: pepperoni pizza dog
directions: Take a warm flour tortilla and put wiener in it.
Add pizza sauce, cheese and pepperoni slices.
Roll tortilla up to secure ingredients so they don't fall out.
Put on microwave-safe plate and put in microwave for 35 seconds on High setting or until cheese has melted.
Take out and eat!

title: easy and delicious poppy seed cake
directions: Blend & mix well, I use an electric beater. Pour into a bundt cake pan which has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: In a large bowl, mix together peanut butter, powdered sugar, butter and graham cracker crumbs.
When thoroughly mixed, roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheets lined with aluminum foil.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Using a double boiler, melt paraffin wax and chocolate chips.
Using a toothpick, dip balls halfway into chocolate mixture.
Store cookies in the refrigerator.

title: confederate jumbles
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift flour together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add milk.
Roll and sprinkle with sugar.
Cut and bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil; cool well and add Cool Whip and mandarin oranges (drained).

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Mix sugar in.
Mix in eggs, one at a time.
Add extract and flour, one cup at a time.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rice with beans and jalapenos
directions: Combine water, picante sauce and onions in a 2-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil over high heat.
Stir in rice, beans, pepper and cumin.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 10 minutes.
(Note: Drain and rinse beans.)
Before serving, fluff rice with a fork. Garnish with tomato wedges.

title: lyna's wild rice casserole
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer in large pot for 15 minutes.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch dish and bake 1 1/2 hours, covered, at 350°.
Serves a crowd.

title: summer squash casserole for crock-pot
directions: Toss stuffing mix with butter.
Place 1/2 mix in crock-pot. Add vegetables mixed together.
Combine soup, sour cream and flour.
Pour over vegetables. Top with remaining stuffing.
Cover and cook 7 to 9 hours on low.
To use regular oven, precook squash.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sauteed bananas
directions: Melt the butter in a skillet.
Peel the bananas and cut them in half lengthwise.
Cook over moderate heat for 5 minutes, turning once.
Remove to a dish and spoon the butter from the pan over them.
Sift the confectioners sugar on top.

title: lipton onion potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
In mixing bowl, mix potatoes with enough oil to coat.
Cover with Lipton onion soup mix.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: barbara's cucumber relish
directions: Mix and let come to boil.
Add cucumbers mixture and simmer 15 minutes.
Pack in hot jars.
Let seal.

title: fried okra
directions: In small bowl, whisk together flour and water until smooth. Place okra in large bowl.
Place crumbs in separate large bowl. Pour half the flour mixture over okra.
Toss gently to coat evenly.
Let stand 15 seconds.
Add remaining flour mixture and toss until evenly coated.
Remove okra with slotted spoon and add to crumbs.
Toss gently to coat evenly.
Remove from crumbs and place on tray or baking sheet large enough to hold in a single layer.
Place in freezer until ready to cook.
In deep fryer, heat about 3 inches oil to 350 degrees.
Place frozen breaded okra in frying basket.
Fry 5 to 6 minutes or until golden brown, shaking basket during cooking to prevent clumping.
Drain thoroughly. Serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: granny's peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle 1/2 in baked pie shell.
Mix salt, cornstarch and sugar in pan. Add milk and the yolks of the 3 eggs.
Cook over medium heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir often.
When thick, pour in pie shell. Sprinkle with rest of peanut butter mixture.
Beat egg whites and a little bit of sugar to make meringue.
Cover pie with meringue. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: lil' bitty burger bundles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix meat, soup mix, egg, pepper, water and bread crumbs.
Press onto 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Prick mixture with fork.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes, or until meat is done. Drain.
Place cheese slices over meat.
Bake 1 minute or until cheese begins to melt.
Cut into 24 squares.
For each sandwich, cover bottom half of dinner roll with burger square, pickle slice and remaining dinner roll half.
Makes cute little burgers for your cute little rascals!

title: philly 3-step cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs and mix well.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: decorating frosting
directions: Beat 3 ingredients together for a stiff consistency.
Enjoy!!!

title: chesapeake bay scrambled eggs
directions: Beat eggs and milk together in a bowl.
Scramble eggs. Sprinkle Old Bay seasoning to taste.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in a medium saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients except vanilla.
Stir over medium-low heat until it comes to a boil.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into a cooled, baked pie shell.
Add meringue.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Blend margarine and cheese together; add flour, Rice Krispies, salt and pepper.
Roll into small balls.
Put on ungreased sheet. Mash down with finger; bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Store in airtight container (can be frozen).

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat peanut butter, cream cheese, 10x sugar and milk together until smooth with electric mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and freeze.
Remove 15 minutes before serving.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well and store in airtight container.
(Empty coffee can with plastic seal works well.)
Use 1/3 cup of mixture and fill with hot water.
Makes enough mix for about 60 cups.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, sift dry ingredients together.
Stir in pecans.
In another bowl beat eggs slightly.
Beat in oil; stir in bananas, pineapple and vanilla. Grease and flour two loaf pans. Mix the banana mixture into dry ingredients.
Pour batter into loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Allow cakes to cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely on wire rack.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Boil beans 25 minutes on stove.
Transfer beans, water and all to a 4-quart
crock-pot sprayed with Pam.
Add brown sugar, oleo and salt, stirring to distribute evenly. Cook on low overnight, covered.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Bring beans to a boil in water; cover and simmer for 2 hours. Melt margarine in skillet; add onion, celery, parsley and garlic. Saut until tender; add to beans. Add rest of ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes, uncovered, stirring occasionally. Serves 12.

title: tina's chicken
directions: Fry cut-up chicken till golden brown.
Put the chopped onions, peppers, and garlic clove with the juice in your pot or casserole dish.
Salt and pepper and top with oregano.
Cook or bake at low temperature till done.
You may put potatoes with it if you wish.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add rice, soup, celery and onion. Melt Cheez Whiz in microwave.
Pour over casserole.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven, uncovered.

title: chop suey
directions: Sear diced meat in skillet until brown.
Mix soy sauce and water.
Add to meat, simmer 2 minutes.
Cook celery and onion in small amount of water until tender.
Add meat, simmer 1 1/2 hours. Mix cornstarch with water to form paste.
Stir in meat mixture, add bean sprouts and mushrooms (also water chestnuts or bamboo shoots if desired).
Cook gently until thick.
Season to taste with salt.
Serve with chow mein noodles or fluffy rice, or both.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Wrap potatoes in aluminum foil and bake 1 hour at 350° or until soft.
To serve unwrap, split open, add butter or margarine and 1 t. brown sugar.
Serves 4.

title: dilly beans
directions: Pack beans in jars.
Add spices and garlic.
Mix vinegar, water and salt in saucepan; bring to a boil and pour over beans. Seal with canning lids and process.
Makes about 7 pints.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a medium-sized mixing bowl, beat eggs, cream, salt, pepper and nutmeg with an eggbeater or a whisk.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Dissolve baking soda in hot water.
Combine all ingredients. Form dough into a ball.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake at 350° to 375° for 10 minutes.

title: buffalo rouladen
directions: Season 6 pieces of steak lightly with salt and pepper.
Divide onion and bacon evenly and place on top of steaks, then top with pickle halves.
Roll each one and secure with toothpicks or skewers.
Brown in lightly oiled skillet.

title: toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Beat butter, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla in a large bowl with electric
mixer
at
high
speed until moist, crumbly and mixture begins
to
gather
around beater; stir in flour until blended. Press batter evenly in prepared pan.

title: cinnamon raisin scone sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 450. Mix all ingredients until soft dough forms. Turn dough onto surface generously dusted with baking mix.; gently roll in baking mix to coat. Knead 5 times.

title: potato skins
directions: Bake one potato in microwave for 4-6 minutes.
Remove from oven after baking.
Wrap in foil and let stand 5 - 10 minutes. Unwrap potato and cut in half length wise.
Hot potatoes are easier to handle if allowed to cool at this point.

Gently scrape out the insides of the potato, do not scrape all the way to the skin (leave a little potato around the edges and on the bottom). Reserve scrapings for another meal, if desired. Season potato skins with seasoned salt and pepper.
Sprinkle green onion on each one. Place in small pan sprayed with the cooking spray.
Lightly spray the potato skins with cooking spray so they will brown nicely. Place under broiler until golden brown.
Remove from broiler and spread inside of each potato skin with one (1) Tbsp. of lite sour cream.
Serve warm.
Two servings.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and chopped onions in margarine for about 15 minutes.
Add cheese and chicken soup.
Cook Minute rice and add to broccoli mixture.

title: fried cheese sticks
directions: Remove cheese from refrigerator 30 to 60 minutes before starting
recipe.
Cut cheese into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Cut slices into 1 to
1/2-inch
pieces.
Mix
cornmeal
mixture coating all sides.	Cover loosely and refrigerate for 3 hours. Heat oil in saucepan or
deep
fryer
Place 6 cheese sticks into hot oil
and
fry.
Turn occasionally until golden brown (about 1 to 2
minutes)
and	drain.	Serve hot or cold. Do not over fry or
cheese
will
leak
out.
Makes
about
20 appetizers.

title: chicken dijon
directions: In skillet in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned; remove.
Pour off fat.
In same skillet, combine soup, water, mustard and pepper; heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover; cook over low heat 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring often.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients except buns and Mozzarella cheese in mixing bowl.
Knead all together by hand.
Place buns open-faced on cookie sheet.
Press patties onto each bun half.
Bake in oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Five minutes before done, place a slice of Mozzarella on each burger and return to oven to melt. Let cool several minutes before tasting.
Makes at least 8 burgers.

title: pork chops
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip chops in buttermilk.
Dredge with the flour, salt and pepper mix.
Cook in the shortening over medium heat.
When brown, turn and brown other side.
A cast-iron skillet gives a more even heat.

title: super duper barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and simmer slowly in covered pan for 1/2 to 1 hour before use.

title: magic jambalaya
directions: Saut carrots and zucchini in margarine in 10-inch skillet over medium heat for 3 minutes. Add tomatoes and juice, mushrooms, water, basil, thyme and kielbasa. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes. Stir in rice. Cover; remove from heat and let stand 8 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes. Season with hot sauce to taste. Serves 5.

title: old fashioned egg salad
directions: In a bowl, combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir in eggs and celery.
Cover and chill.
For each serving, spoon about 1/2 cup on lettuce leaf or bread.

title: marinated brussels sprouts
directions: Prepare dressing as directed on package.
Cook Brussels sprouts as directed; drain off liquid.
Pour prepared dressing over hot, cooked sprouts.
Marinate at least overnight.

title: chestnut dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Make into patties and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pickled red beet eggs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except eggs; heat to boiling.
Cool. Place hard-boiled eggs into a large gallon glass jar.
Pour red beets and brine over eggs.
Allow to sit in refrigerator for at least 24 hours before serving with salt and pepper.

title: pineapple-cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl with fork, beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually stir in crushed pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in remaining nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap or foil.
Refrigerate until well chilled overnight.

title: chocolate-strawberry torte
directions: Place in 12-quart punch bowl. Bake cake according to directions. Cut cake into cubes. Done in layers. Mix strawberries with glaze and whipped topping, 3 1/2 cups. Heat frosting until pourable. Drizzle over topping. Repeat layers.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except parsley and nuts.
Shape into ball.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
When ready to serve, mix nuts and parsley.
Roll ball in mixture.

title: tortilla breakfast pockets
directions: On a cookie sheet, lay flat the desired number of tortillas per person.
Heat at 300° for 5 minutes.
Add hot scrambled eggs to each tortilla.
Add cheese and salsa.
Fold tortilla.
Serve warm.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and add cranberry jelly.
Beat with an eggbeater until smooth.
Add lemon juice and freeze.

title: remoulade sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Can be served over boiled shrimp, salad and fish.

title: gazpacho
directions: In a blender, combine half the cucumber, one tomato, half the green pepper, half the onion, the whole pimento and 1 cup tomato juice.
Puree at high speed.
Set aside.
Chop the remaining cucumber, tomato, green pepper and onion.
Place in a bowl; cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Pour the puree into a large serving bowl and add 2 cups tomato juice, vinegar, oil, Tabasco sauce, salt, pepper and garlic.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours. Just before serving, add reserved chopped vegetables to the pureed mixture.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook zucchini and onion in salt water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrots; fold in zucchini and onion.
Spread half of the dressing mixed with butter and cheese in the bottom of a glass baking dish.
Spoon in vegetable mix and then top with rest of dressing mix.
Sprinkle Colby cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: refrigerator date cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar thoroughly; add eggs 1 at a time and beat well after each addition.
Add nuts and dates.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture and mix well. Shape in rolls 2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper and store in refrigerator until firm.
Slice thin and bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Makes 11 to 12 dozen cookies.

title: party mix
directions: In a roaster, mix the first 5 ingredients (you may use any cereal you wish).
Heat the remaining ingredients (sprinkle some Season-All on, if you wish).
Pour mixture over mixed cereal, gradually stirring or mixing well.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: bacon quiche biscuit cups
directions: In small bowl, beat cream cheese, milk and eggs on low speed until smooth.
Stir in Swiss cheese and onions; set aside.

title: frank's red beans and rice
directions: Cover beans with water and soak overnight or 6 to 8 hours. Drain beans.
Wash and place in large pot with ham hock and 2 quarts of water.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: smoked sausage and horseradish
directions: Cut 2 circles (2 inches each) from each slice of bread using biscuit cutter.
Toast 1 side of bread rounds under broiler.
Mix together sausage, sour cream, horseradish and flour.
Spread untoasted side of each bread circle with sausage mixture.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Makes 32 canapes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in fridge to chill.

title: "spiders"
directions: Place peanut butter and morsels over hot water until morsels melt. Stir until melted. Add noodles and coat. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper on cookie sheet. Chill until set. Chips of candied cherries (red and green) on tops are nice for Christmas plates.

title: new england fish chowder
directions: Melt butter and saute onion to light brown. Drain butter into saucepan.
Add potatoes and 1 pint boiling water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add fish and simmer 20 minutes.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling point.

title: american berry no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Gently stir in 2 cups of the Cool Whip. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 3 hours or until set. Spread remaining Cool Whip over cheesecake.
Arrange berries in rows on top of cheesecake to resemble a flag or other desired design.

title: biscuiti regina(seeded cookies)
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut Crisco into ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla, making into a soft dough.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Bake in 2
layers. When done, place berries between and on top of cake.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef until well done.
Brown onion and peppers. Combine with ground beef.
Add spaghetti and enough water to simmer slowly for 20 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: wop - slop
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Brown and drain ground beef. Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until cheese is browned and melted.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, shape into ball.
Roll into chopped nuts.

title: fudge truffle cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
Mix crust ingredients and put into springform pan.
For chocolate crust, add 1/3 cup Hershey's cocoa.

title: chocolate chip apple cake
directions: Cream the sugars and shortening together.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk. Add diced apples.
Mix chocolate chips, cinnamon and white sugar. Sprinkle over above mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and 1 stick oleo together and pat into bottom of oblong pan that has been sprayed with Pam or shortening and floured.
Combine cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar together and spread mixture over crust in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan; add 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick and clear. Remove from heat and add jello.
Stir until completely dissolved. Place strawberries in baked crust.
Pour hot mixture over strawberries.
Chill.
May be served with whipped topping.
This is quick, easy and delicious!

title: sour cream sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and green pepper in skillet.
Add tomatoes, sour cream and chili powder.
Add this to cooked macaroni and pour into large casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until liquid is absorbed.
Serves 6.

title: noodle pizza
directions: Layer noodles, hamburger, sauce and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then make second layer of each.
Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: lemonade salad
directions: Mix together and pour over graham cracker crust.

title: cherry fruit squares
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, vanilla, eggs and flour.
Spread 3/4 of batter on a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Pour in filling. Place rest of batter on top.
Spread a little.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with sugar after baking, if desired.

title: russian fluff
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Add celery, peas and cooked rice.
Put into large casserole.
Mix tomato soup with equal water.
Add catsup.
Pour over ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pancit bihon guisado(sauteed rice sticks)
directions: Cover chicken with water in a pot and bring to a boil.
Add chopped green onions and salt.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Drain, but save broth.
Remove meat from chicken and cut into small pieces.

title: muriel's mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes as usual.
Saute onion.
Drain potatoes and mash with margarine and cream cheese until blended.
Add onion and mix. Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
If potatoes are too thick, add milk until creamy.
Serves a lot.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Blend brown sugar, flour, oats, cinnamon, nutmeg and butter until crumbly. Spread over apples.
Bake in oven at 350° until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.

title: make ahead breakfast bake
directions: Crumble sausage in a medium skillet.
Cook over medium heat until brown; drain well.
Spread bread cubes in a buttered 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish and top with sausage and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Beat well and pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pea-bean salad
directions: Toss and chill overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: sugar-free fat-free pumpkin pie
directions: Whisk the pudding mix in cold milk.
Stir in pumpkin and spices.
Pour into pie shell and chill.
Top with nonfat topping.

title: corn salad
directions: Open both cans of Shoe Peg corn and put into a medium mixing bowl (do not cook).
Chop up the onions and tops, bell pepper and tomatoes.
Mix well into the corn.
Add 1/2 bottle of Green Goddess salad dressing and mix well.
Chill slightly.
Ready to serve.

title: pilaf
directions: Place oleo in saucepan and brown uncooked noodles until light golden brown.
Pour in soup, water and rice.
Bring to boil and simmer about 20 minutes or until rice is tender and moisture evaporated.
You may have to add some water before rice is tender, so watch for that near the end of cooking time.

title: pesto genovese
directions: In electric blender, blend all ingredients except the oil to a smooth paste.
Slowly blend in oil and stir until smooth.
Serve with hot pasta; toss pasta with 1 to 2 tablespoons butter with pesto to taste.
Leftovers may be placed in a small jar, covered with olive oil and refrigerated.
Makes about 3/4 to 1 cup sauce.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add egg and molasses. Beat thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with water, beating after each addition.
Bake in greased and lightly floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: brownie trifle
directions: Prepare mix and bake according to directions.
After cooled, break into pieces.
Prepare pudding according to directions, omitting chilling.
In 3-quart trifle dish, place 1/3 of crumbled brownies.
Follow with 1/3 of pudding and 1/3 of Cool Whip topping.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
End with whipped topping on top layer.
Garnish top with chocolate curls from candy bar.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Cook beef and onion over medium-high heat, stirring often until beef is brown.
Drain.
Stir in vegetables, thyme and undiluted soups.
Mix.
Peel and shred potatoes.
Cook in melted butter until brown.
Place on top of meat mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Make into small balls. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in a small pan.
Use a toothpick to dip balls in chocolate mixture.
Place on waxed paper to cool completely.
Refrigerate if you want.

title: crunchy cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape into small balls, using hands. Flatten biscuits.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 40 biscuits.

title: louisiana style hot sauce
directions: Blend tomatoes in blender.
Add other ingredients and blend together.
Can be used with tortilla chips or as a sauce over tacos and/or burritos.

title: easy chicken tortilla bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken breasts in deep skillet. Add water to barely cover.
Bring to a simmer and cook over medium heat until chicken is white throughout, but still moist, 12-15 minutes.
Drain.
When cool enough to handle, tear into 1 inch strips and layer in a greased 9x13 inch baking dish. Layer tortilla strips evenly over chicken.

title: pie pastry
directions: Combine 1 2/3 cups flour and the salt in medium-size bowl. Add shortening; work into flour by rubbing rapidly between fingers until mixture resembles peas.

title: savory zucchini roll
directions: Pat zucchini to absorb moisture with paper towel.
In skillet, saute zucchini and onion in magarine for 5 minutes.
Separate dough into 2 long rectangles.
Press or roll to form a 12 x 8-inch rectangle, sealing perforations.
Spread filling evenly over dough. Sprinkle cheese on top of zucchini filling, starting at longest side, roll up and seal edges.
Place, seam side down, on greased cookie sheet.
With sharp knife, make cuts at 1-inch intervals halfway through roll.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions and cool. Mix and cream together the cream cheese, pudding and milk. Spread over cooled cake. Top cake with crushed, drained pineapple, then spread Cool Whip over pineapple. Sprinkle coconut over top of cake. Keep cake chilled.

title: hidden valley salad
directions: Tear spinach and lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Layer lettuce, spinach, green pepper, bacon, mushrooms, green onions and eggs in large bowl.

title: blowout cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Set aside.
Beat peanut butter and butter until fluffy.
Add sugars and beat until smooth.
Stir in flour.
Mix and beat to soften dough.
Fold in chips and peanuts carefully.
Add peanut butter cups.

title: sweet marinated cucumbers
directions: Boil water, vinegar, salt, pepper and sugar together for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Peel cucumbers and slice thin.
Cover with cooled brine and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
(Onions can also be added.)

title: cowboy caviar
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well. Cover and chill overnight.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix everything together.
Use liquid from roast chicken to moisten or just add a little water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or in crock-pot.

title: old-fashioned buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk. Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.

title: layered taco dip
directions: In large skillet, brown meat. Pour off fat. Add chilies and bouillon. Cook and stir until bouillon dissolves. Cool. In small bowl, combine sour cream and taco seasoning mix; set aside.

title: potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Add ingredients in a large plastic bag. Close bag and shake.
Empty bag into shallow baking pan; discard bag.
Bake, stirring occasionally; 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate dipped potato chips
directions: Melt the chocolate chips in one container.

title: stir-fried broccoli and carrots
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet or wok over medium heat.
Add broccoli, carrots and onions; stir-fry until tender-crisp.
Add water chestnuts.

title: chocolate cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Stir in the oil, buttermilk and eggs. Add the water and stir until well mixed. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 38 minutes or until toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Frost with the following Caramel Icing.

title: cinnamon-sugar tortillas
directions: In small bowl, combine cinnamon and sugar and mix well.
In large skillet, heat 1/2 inch of oil over medium heat until haze forms.
Fry tortilla quarters a few at a time, for 1 minute or until golden.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.

title: vegetable medley salad
directions: Combine cauliflower, broccoli, onion, mushrooms, water chestnuts, olives and peppers.
Cover with Italian dressing; refrigerate and marinate overnight.
Drain Italian dressing off of vegetables before serving.
Serves 15.

title: peach crisp
directions: Arrange peaches in a slightly greased dish.
Blend sugar, flour, spices and butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches. Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping, if desired.

title: gravy for rice or dressing
directions: Melt margarine on low; add flour. Add broth and cook until thick.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; let sit for 10 minutes.
Add sugars, margarine and eggs; set aside.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cocoa together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Pour mixture into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup chocolate chips and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender in a small amount of water.
Drain. Combine carrots, onion and green pepper.
Set aside.

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Mix up chocolate cake as directed.
Grease and flour pan 9 x 13 x 2-inch.
Pour half in pan and bake for 15 minutes.
Melt butter, caramels and milk.
Pour on top of cake.
Pour rest of cake batter on top of caramel mixture and bake until done.
Cool and frost with chocolate frosting.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: saucy chicken casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan, combine soups, sour cream, broth, onion, mushrooms and seasonings.
Arrange chicken on top of sauce.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serve chicken and sauce over noodles or rice.
Garnish with parsley.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: *Sour Milk:
Add 1/2 teaspoon vinegar to 4 tablespoons milk; let stand for 15 minutes.

title: green chilies enchilada
directions: Brown ground beef, add seasoning, soup, milk and onions. Layer into greased casserole with chilies and cheese reserving part of cheese for top.
Warm in oven until cheese melts.
Serve over Dorito chips.

title: coconut chicken with fresh fruit
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook 4 minutes on each side or until lightly browned. Sprinkle with ginger, salt and 3 tablespoons coconut; add cream. Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Arrange chicken, bananas and papaya on a large serving platter.
Pour warm sauce over chicken and sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine butter, 2 cups flour and 10x sugar. Put into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
